222  template<typename T> struct has_##type { \

274 // implementation of C++14 index_sequence and affiliates
275 // source: https://stackoverflow.com/a/32223343
276 template<std::size_t... Ints>
277 struct index_sequence
278 {
279  using type = index_sequence;
280  using value_type = std::size_t;
281  static constexpr std::size_t size() noexcept
282  {
283  return sizeof...(Ints);
284  }
285 };

287 template<class Sequence1, class Sequence2>
288 struct merge_and_renumber;
289 
290 template<std::size_t... I1, std::size_t... I2>
291 struct merge_and_renumber<index_sequence<I1...>, index_sequence<I2...>>
292  : index_sequence < I1..., (sizeof...(I1) + I2)... > {};
293 
294 template<std::size_t N>
295 struct make_index_sequence
296  : merge_and_renumber < typename make_index_sequence < N / 2 >::type,
297  typename make_index_sequence < N - N / 2 >::type > {};
298 
299 template<> struct make_index_sequence<0> : index_sequence<> {};
300 template<> struct make_index_sequence<1> : index_sequence<0> {};
301 
302 template<typename... Ts>
303 using index_sequence_for = make_index_sequence<sizeof...(Ts)>;

305 /*
306 Implementation of two C++17 constructs: conjunction, negation. This is needed
307 to avoid evaluating all the traits in a condition
308 
309 For example: not std::is_same<void, T>::value and has_value_type<T>::value
310 will not compile when T = void (on MSVC at least). Whereas
311 conjunction<negation<std::is_same<void, T>>, has_value_type<T>>::value will
312 stop evaluating if negation<...>::value == false
313 
314 Please note that those constructs must be used with caution, since symbols can
315 become very long quickly (which can slow down compilation and cause MSVC
316 internal compiler errors). Only use it when you have to (see example ahead).
317 */
318 template<class...> struct conjunction : std::true_type {};
319 template<class B1> struct conjunction<B1> : B1 {};
320 template<class B1, class... Bn>
321 struct conjunction<B1, Bn...> : std::conditional<bool(B1::value), conjunction<Bn...>, B1>::type {};
322 
323 template<class B> struct negation : std::integral_constant<bool, not B::value> {};
324 
325 // dispatch utility (taken from ranges-v3)
326 template<unsigned N> struct priority_tag : priority_tag < N - 1 > {};
327 template<> struct priority_tag<0> {};

346 template<bool B, class RealType, class CompatibleObjectType>
347 struct is_compatible_object_type_impl : std::false_type {};
348 
349 template<class RealType, class CompatibleObjectType>
350 struct is_compatible_object_type_impl<true, RealType, CompatibleObjectType>
351 {
352  static constexpr auto value =
353  std::is_constructible<typename RealType::key_type, typename CompatibleObjectType::key_type>::value and
354  std::is_constructible<typename RealType::mapped_type, typename CompatibleObjectType::mapped_type>::value;
355 };
356 
357 template<class BasicJsonType, class CompatibleObjectType>
358 struct is_compatible_object_type
359 {
360  static auto constexpr value = is_compatible_object_type_impl <
361  conjunction<negation<std::is_same<void, CompatibleObjectType>>,
362  has_mapped_type<CompatibleObjectType>,
363  has_key_type<CompatibleObjectType>>::value,
364  typename BasicJsonType::object_t, CompatibleObjectType >::value;
365 };
366 
367 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
368 struct is_basic_json_nested_type
369 {
370  static auto constexpr value = std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::iterator>::value or
371  std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::const_iterator>::value or
372  std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::reverse_iterator>::value or
373  std::is_same<T, typename BasicJsonType::const_reverse_iterator>::value;
374 };
375 
376 template<class BasicJsonType, class CompatibleArrayType>
377 struct is_compatible_array_type
378 {
379  static auto constexpr value =
380  conjunction<negation<std::is_same<void, CompatibleArrayType>>,
381  negation<is_compatible_object_type<
382  BasicJsonType, CompatibleArrayType>>,
383  negation<std::is_constructible<typename BasicJsonType::string_t,
384  CompatibleArrayType>>,
385  negation<is_basic_json_nested_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleArrayType>>,
386  has_value_type<CompatibleArrayType>,
387  has_iterator<CompatibleArrayType>>::value;
388 };
389 
390 template<bool, typename, typename>
391 struct is_compatible_integer_type_impl : std::false_type {};
392 
393 template<typename RealIntegerType, typename CompatibleNumberIntegerType>
394 struct is_compatible_integer_type_impl<true, RealIntegerType, CompatibleNumberIntegerType>
395 {
396  // is there an assert somewhere on overflows?
397  using RealLimits = std::numeric_limits<RealIntegerType>;
398  using CompatibleLimits = std::numeric_limits<CompatibleNumberIntegerType>;
399 
400  static constexpr auto value =
401  std::is_constructible<RealIntegerType, CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value and
402  CompatibleLimits::is_integer and
403  RealLimits::is_signed == CompatibleLimits::is_signed;
404 };
405 
406 template<typename RealIntegerType, typename CompatibleNumberIntegerType>
407 struct is_compatible_integer_type
408 {
409  static constexpr auto value =
410  is_compatible_integer_type_impl <
411  std::is_integral<CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value and
412  not std::is_same<bool, CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value,
413  RealIntegerType, CompatibleNumberIntegerType > ::value;
414 };

416 // trait checking if JSONSerializer<T>::from_json(json const&, udt&) exists
417 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
418 struct has_from_json
419 {
420  private:
421  // also check the return type of from_json
422  template<typename U, typename = enable_if_t<std::is_same<void, decltype(uncvref_t<U>::from_json(
423  std::declval<BasicJsonType>(), std::declval<T&>()))>::value>>
424  static int detect(U&&);
425  static void detect(...);
426 
427  public:
428  static constexpr bool value = std::is_integral<decltype(
429  detect(std::declval<typename BasicJsonType::template json_serializer<T, void>>()))>::value;
430 };
431 
432 // This trait checks if JSONSerializer<T>::from_json(json const&) exists
433 // this overload is used for non-default-constructible user-defined-types
434 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
435 struct has_non_default_from_json
436 {
437  private:
438  template <
439  typename U,
440  typename = enable_if_t<std::is_same<
441  T, decltype(uncvref_t<U>::from_json(std::declval<BasicJsonType>()))>::value >>
442  static int detect(U&&);
443  static void detect(...);
444 
445  public:
446  static constexpr bool value = std::is_integral<decltype(detect(
447  std::declval<typename BasicJsonType::template json_serializer<T, void>>()))>::value;
448 };
449 
450 // This trait checks if BasicJsonType::json_serializer<T>::to_json exists
451 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
452 struct has_to_json
453 {
454  private:
455  template<typename U, typename = decltype(uncvref_t<U>::to_json(
456  std::declval<BasicJsonType&>(), std::declval<T>()))>
457  static int detect(U&&);
458  static void detect(...);
459 
460  public:
461  static constexpr bool value = std::is_integral<decltype(detect(
462  std::declval<typename BasicJsonType::template json_serializer<T, void>>()))>::value;
463 };

465 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleCompleteType>
466 struct is_compatible_complete_type
467 {
468  static constexpr bool value =
469  not std::is_base_of<std::istream, CompatibleCompleteType>::value and
470  not is_basic_json<CompatibleCompleteType>::value and
471  not is_basic_json_nested_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleCompleteType>::value and
472  has_to_json<BasicJsonType, CompatibleCompleteType>::value;
473 };

537 class exception : public std::exception
538 {
539  public:
541  const char* what() const noexcept override
542  {
543  return m.what();
544  }
545 
547  const int id;
548 
549  protected:
550  exception(int id_, const char* what_arg) : id(id_), m(what_arg) {}
551 
552  static std::string name(const std::string& ename, int id_)
553  {
554  return "[json.exception." + ename + "." + std::to_string(id_) + "] ";
555  }
556 
557  private:
559  std::runtime_error m;
560 };
561 
605 class parse_error : public exception
606 {
607  public:
616  static parse_error create(int id_, std::size_t byte_, const std::string& what_arg)
617  {
618  std::string w = exception::name("parse_error", id_) + "parse error" +
619  (byte_ != 0 ? (" at " + std::to_string(byte_)) : "") +
620  ": " + what_arg;
621  return parse_error(id_, byte_, w.c_str());
622  }
623 
633  const std::size_t byte;
634 
635  private:
636  parse_error(int id_, std::size_t byte_, const char* what_arg)
637  : exception(id_, what_arg), byte(byte_) {}
638 };

834 namespace nlohmann

836 namespace detail

839 // JSON type enumeration //
841 
866 enum class value_t : std::uint8_t
867 {
868  null,
869  object,
870  array,
871  string,
872  boolean,
873  number_integer,
874  number_unsigned,
875  number_float,
876  discarded
877 };
878 
889 inline bool operator<(const value_t lhs, const value_t rhs) noexcept
890 {
891  static constexpr std::array<std::uint8_t, 8> order = {{
892  0 /* null */, 3 /* object */, 4 /* array */, 5 /* string */,
893  1 /* boolean */, 2 /* integer */, 2 /* unsigned */, 2 /* float */
894  }
895  };
896 
897  const auto l_index = static_cast<std::size_t>(lhs);
898  const auto r_index = static_cast<std::size_t>(rhs);
899  return l_index < order.size() and r_index < order.size() and order[l_index] < order[r_index];
900 }
901 }
902 }

924 // #include <nlohmann/detail/value_t.hpp>
925 
926 
927 namespace nlohmann
928 {
929 namespace detail
930 {
931 // overloads for basic_json template parameters
932 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename ArithmeticType,
933  enable_if_t<std::is_arithmetic<ArithmeticType>::value and
934  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t>::value,
935  int> = 0>
936 void get_arithmetic_value(const BasicJsonType& j, ArithmeticType& val)
937 {
938  switch (static_cast<value_t>(j))
939  {
940  case value_t::number_unsigned:
941  {
942  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t*>());
943  break;
944  }
945  case value_t::number_integer:
946  {
947  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t*>());
948  break;
949  }
950  case value_t::number_float:
951  {
952  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t*>());
953  break;
954  }
955 
956  default:
957  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be number, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
958  }
959 }
960 
961 template<typename BasicJsonType>
962 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t& b)
963 {
964  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_boolean()))
965  {
966  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be boolean, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
967  }
968  b = *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t*>();
969 }

977  }

1008 template<typename BasicJsonType>
1009 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::array_t& arr)
1010 {
1011  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array()))
1012  {
1013  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1014  }

1018 // forward_list doesn't have an insert method
1019 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T, typename Allocator,
1020  enable_if_t<std::is_convertible<BasicJsonType, T>::value, int> = 0>
1021 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::forward_list<T, Allocator>& l)
1022 {
1023  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array()))
1024  {
1025  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1026  }
1027  std::transform(j.rbegin(), j.rend(),
1028  std::front_inserter(l), [](const BasicJsonType & i)
1029  {
1030  return i.template get<T>();
1031  });
1032 }
1033 
1034 // valarray doesn't have an insert method
1035 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T,
1036  enable_if_t<std::is_convertible<BasicJsonType, T>::value, int> = 0>
1037 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::valarray<T>& l)
1038 {
1039  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array()))
1040  {
1041  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1042  }
1043  l.resize(j.size());
1044  std::copy(j.m_value.array->begin(), j.m_value.array->end(), std::begin(l));
1045 }
1046 
1047 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType>
1048 void from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, CompatibleArrayType& arr, priority_tag<0> /*unused*/)
1049 {
1050  using std::end;
1051 
1052  std::transform(j.begin(), j.end(),
1053  std::inserter(arr, end(arr)), [](const BasicJsonType & i)
1054  {
1055  // get<BasicJsonType>() returns *this, this won't call a from_json
1056  // method when value_type is BasicJsonType
1057  return i.template get<typename CompatibleArrayType::value_type>();
1058  });
1059 }
1060 
1061 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType>
1062 auto from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, CompatibleArrayType& arr, priority_tag<1> /*unused*/)
1063 -> decltype(
1064  arr.reserve(std::declval<typename CompatibleArrayType::size_type>()),
1065  void())
1066 {
1067  using std::end;
1068 
1069  arr.reserve(j.size());
1070  std::transform(j.begin(), j.end(),
1071  std::inserter(arr, end(arr)), [](const BasicJsonType & i)
1072  {
1073  // get<BasicJsonType>() returns *this, this won't call a from_json
1074  // method when value_type is BasicJsonType
1075  return i.template get<typename CompatibleArrayType::value_type>();
1076  });
1077 }
1078 
1079 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T, std::size_t N>
1080 void from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, std::array<T, N>& arr, priority_tag<2> /*unused*/)
1081 {
1082  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < N; ++i)
1083  {
1084  arr[i] = j.at(i).template get<T>();
1085  }
1086 }

1088 template <
1089  typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType,
1090  enable_if_t <
1091  is_compatible_array_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleArrayType>::value and
1092  not std::is_same<typename BasicJsonType::array_t,
1093  CompatibleArrayType>::value and
1094  std::is_constructible <
1095  BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType::value_type >::value,
1096  int > = 0 >
1097 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, CompatibleArrayType& arr)
1098 {
1099  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array()))
1100  {
1101  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " +
1102  std::string(j.type_name())));
1103  }
1104 
1105  from_json_array_impl(j, arr, priority_tag<2> {});
1106 }
1107 
1108 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleObjectType,
1109  enable_if_t<is_compatible_object_type<BasicJsonType, CompatibleObjectType>::value, int> = 0>
1110 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, CompatibleObjectType& obj)
1111 {
1112  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_object()))
1113  {
1114  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be object, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1115  }
1116 
1117  auto inner_object = j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::object_t*>();
1118  using value_type = typename CompatibleObjectType::value_type;
1119  std::transform(
1120  inner_object->begin(), inner_object->end(),
1121  std::inserter(obj, obj.begin()),
1122  [](typename BasicJsonType::object_t::value_type const & p)
1123  {
1124  return value_type(p.first, p.second.template get<typename CompatibleObjectType::mapped_type>());
1125  });
1126 }
1127 
1128 // overload for arithmetic types, not chosen for basic_json template arguments
1129 // (BooleanType, etc..); note: Is it really necessary to provide explicit
1130 // overloads for boolean_t etc. in case of a custom BooleanType which is not
1131 // an arithmetic type?
1132 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename ArithmeticType,
1133  enable_if_t <
1134  std::is_arithmetic<ArithmeticType>::value and
1135  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t>::value and
1136  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t>::value and
1137  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t>::value and
1138  not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t>::value,
1139  int> = 0>
1140 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, ArithmeticType& val)
1141 {
1142  switch (static_cast<value_t>(j))
1143  {
1144  case value_t::number_unsigned:
1145  {
1146  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t*>());
1147  break;
1148  }
1149  case value_t::number_integer:
1150  {
1151  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t*>());
1152  break;
1153  }
1154  case value_t::number_float:
1155  {
1156  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t*>());
1157  break;
1158  }
1159  case value_t::boolean:
1160  {
1161  val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t*>());
1162  break;
1163  }
1164 
1165  default:
1166  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be number, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1167  }
1168 }
1169 
1170 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename A1, typename A2>
1171 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::pair<A1, A2>& p)
1172 {
1173  p = {j.at(0).template get<A1>(), j.at(1).template get<A2>()};
1174 }
1175 
1176 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename Tuple, std::size_t... Idx>
1177 void from_json_tuple_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, Tuple& t, index_sequence<Idx...>)
1178 {
1179  t = std::make_tuple(j.at(Idx).template get<typename std::tuple_element<Idx, Tuple>::type>()...);
1180 }
1181 
1182 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename... Args>
1183 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::tuple<Args...>& t)
1184 {
1185  from_json_tuple_impl(j, t, index_sequence_for<Args...> {});
1186 }
1187 
1188 struct from_json_fn
1189 {
1190  private:
1191  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1192  auto call(const BasicJsonType& j, T& val, priority_tag<1> /*unused*/) const
1193  noexcept(noexcept(from_json(j, val)))
1194  -> decltype(from_json(j, val), void())
1195  {
1196  return from_json(j, val);
1197  }
1198 
1199  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1200  void call(const BasicJsonType& /*unused*/, T& /*unused*/, priority_tag<0> /*unused*/) const noexcept
1201  {
1202  static_assert(sizeof(BasicJsonType) == 0,
1203  "could not find from_json() method in T's namespace");
1204 #ifdef _MSC_VER
1205  // MSVC does not show a stacktrace for the above assert
1206  using decayed = uncvref_t<T>;
1207  static_assert(sizeof(typename decayed::force_msvc_stacktrace) == 0,
1208  "forcing MSVC stacktrace to show which T we're talking about.");
1209 #endif
1210  }
1211 
1212  public:
1213  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1214  void operator()(const BasicJsonType& j, T& val) const
1215  noexcept(noexcept(std::declval<from_json_fn>().call(j, val, priority_tag<1> {})))
1216  {
1217  return call(j, val, priority_tag<1> {});
1218  }
1219 };
1220 }
1221 
1225 namespace
1226 {
1227 constexpr const auto& from_json = detail::static_const<detail::from_json_fn>::value;
1228 }
1229 }

1343 
1344  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType,
1345  enable_if_t<not std::is_same<CompatibleArrayType, typename BasicJsonType::array_t>::value,
1346  int> = 0>
1347  static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, const CompatibleArrayType& arr)
1348  {
1349  using std::begin;
1350  using std::end;
1351  j.m_type = value_t::array;
1352  j.m_value.array = j.template create<typename BasicJsonType::array_t>(begin(arr), end(arr));
1353  j.assert_invariant();
1354  }
1355 
1356  template<typename BasicJsonType>
1357  static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, const std::vector<bool>& arr)
1358  {
1359  j.m_type = value_t::array;
1360  j.m_value = value_t::array;
1361  j.m_value.array->reserve(arr.size());
1362  for (const bool x : arr)
1363  {
1364  j.m_value.array->push_back(x);
1365  }
1366  j.assert_invariant();
1367  }
1368 
1369  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T,
1370  enable_if_t<std::is_convertible<T, BasicJsonType>::value, int> = 0>
1371  static void construct(BasicJsonType& j, const std::valarray<T>& arr)
1372  {
1373  j.m_type = value_t::array;
1374  j.m_value = value_t::array;
1375  j.m_value.array->resize(arr.size());
1376  std::copy(std::begin(arr), std::end(arr), j.m_value.array->begin());
1377  j.assert_invariant();
1378  }
1379 };

1532 struct to_json_fn
1533 {
1534  private:
1535  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1536  auto call(BasicJsonType& j, T&& val, priority_tag<1> /*unused*/) const noexcept(noexcept(to_json(j, std::forward<T>(val))))
1537  -> decltype(to_json(j, std::forward<T>(val)), void())
1538  {

1540  }
1541 
1542  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1543  void call(BasicJsonType& /*unused*/, T&& /*unused*/, priority_tag<0> /*unused*/) const noexcept
1544  {
1545  static_assert(sizeof(BasicJsonType) == 0,
1546  "could not find to_json() method in T's namespace");
1547 
1548 #ifdef _MSC_VER
1549  // MSVC does not show a stacktrace for the above assert
1550  using decayed = uncvref_t<T>;
1551  static_assert(sizeof(typename decayed::force_msvc_stacktrace) == 0,
1552  "forcing MSVC stacktrace to show which T we're talking about.");
1553 #endif
1554  }
1555 
1556  public:
1557  template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1558  void operator()(BasicJsonType& j, T&& val) const
1559  noexcept(noexcept(std::declval<to_json_fn>().call(j, std::forward<T>(val), priority_tag<1> {})))
1560  {
1561  return call(j, std::forward<T>(val), priority_tag<1> {});
1562  }
1563 };
1564 }
1565 
1567 namespace
1568 {
1569 constexpr const auto& to_json = detail::static_const<detail::to_json_fn>::value;
1570 }
1571 }

1600 
1612 struct input_adapter_protocol
1613 {
1615  virtual std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() = 0;
1617  virtual void unget_character() = 0;
1618  virtual ~input_adapter_protocol() = default;
1619 };
1620 
1622 using input_adapter_t = std::shared_ptr<input_adapter_protocol>;
1623 
1633 class input_stream_adapter : public input_adapter_protocol
1634 {
1635  public:
1636  ~input_stream_adapter() override
1637  {
1638  // clear stream flags; we use underlying streambuf I/O, do not
1639  // maintain ifstream flags
1640  is.clear();
1641  }
1642 
1643  explicit input_stream_adapter(std::istream& i)
1644  : is(i), sb(*i.rdbuf())
1645  {
1646  // skip byte order mark
1647  std::char_traits<char>::int_type c;
1648  if ((c = get_character()) == 0xEF)
1649  {
1650  if ((c = get_character()) == 0xBB)
1651  {
1652  if ((c = get_character()) == 0xBF)
1653  {
1654  return; // Ignore BOM
1655  }
1656  else if (c != std::char_traits<char>::eof())
1657  {
1658  is.unget();
1659  }
1660  is.putback('\xBB');
1661  }
1662  else if (c != std::char_traits<char>::eof())
1663  {
1664  is.unget();
1665  }
1666  is.putback('\xEF');
1667  }
1668  else if (c != std::char_traits<char>::eof())
1669  {
1670  is.unget(); // no byte order mark; process as usual
1671  }
1672  }
1673 
1674  // delete because of pointer members
1675  input_stream_adapter(const input_stream_adapter&) = delete;
1676  input_stream_adapter& operator=(input_stream_adapter&) = delete;
1677 
1678  // std::istream/std::streambuf use std::char_traits<char>::to_int_type, to
1679  // ensure that std::char_traits<char>::eof() and the character 0xFF do not
1680  // end up as the same value, eg. 0xFFFFFFFF.
1681  std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() override
1682  {
1683  return sb.sbumpc();
1684  }
1685 
1686  void unget_character() override
1687  {
1688  sb.sungetc(); // is.unget() avoided for performance
1689  }
1690 
1691  private:
1693  std::istream& is;
1694  std::streambuf& sb;
1695 };
1696 
1698 class input_buffer_adapter : public input_adapter_protocol
1699 {
1700  public:
1701  input_buffer_adapter(const char* b, const std::size_t l)
1702  : cursor(b), limit(b + l), start(b)
1703  {
1704  // skip byte order mark
1705  if (l >= 3 and b[0] == '\xEF' and b[1] == '\xBB' and b[2] == '\xBF')
1706  {
1707  cursor += 3;
1708  }
1709  }
1710 
1711  // delete because of pointer members
1712  input_buffer_adapter(const input_buffer_adapter&) = delete;
1713  input_buffer_adapter& operator=(input_buffer_adapter&) = delete;
1714 
1715  std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() noexcept override
1716  {
1717  if (JSON_LIKELY(cursor < limit))
1718  {
1719  return std::char_traits<char>::to_int_type(*(cursor++));
1720  }
1721 
1722  return std::char_traits<char>::eof();
1723  }
1724 
1725  void unget_character() noexcept override
1726  {
1727  if (JSON_LIKELY(cursor > start))
1728  {
1729  --cursor;
1730  }
1731  }
1732 
1733  private:
1735  const char* cursor;
1737  const char* limit;
1739  const char* start;
1740 };
1741 
1742 template<typename WideStringType>
1743 class wide_string_input_adapter : public input_adapter_protocol
1744 {
1745  public:
1746  wide_string_input_adapter(const WideStringType& w) : str(w) {}
1747 
1748  std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() noexcept override
1749  {
1750  // unget_character() was called previously: return the last character
1751  if (next_unget)
1752  {
1753  next_unget = false;
1754  return last_char;
1755  }
1756 
1757  // check if buffer needs to be filled
1758  if (utf8_bytes_index == utf8_bytes_filled)
1759  {
1760  if (sizeof(typename WideStringType::value_type) == 2)
1761  {
1762  fill_buffer_utf16();
1763  }
1764  else
1765  {
1766  fill_buffer_utf32();
1767  }
1768 
1769  assert(utf8_bytes_filled > 0);
1770  assert(utf8_bytes_index == 0);
1771  }
1772 
1773  // use buffer
1774  assert(utf8_bytes_filled > 0);
1775  assert(utf8_bytes_index < utf8_bytes_filled);
1776  return (last_char = utf8_bytes[utf8_bytes_index++]);
1777  }
1778 
1779  void unget_character() noexcept override
1780  {
1781  next_unget = true;
1782  }
1783 
1784  private:
1785  void fill_buffer_utf16()
1786  {
1787  utf8_bytes_index = 0;
1788 
1789  if (current_wchar == str.size())
1790  {
1791  utf8_bytes[0] = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
1792  utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
1793  }
1794  else
1795  {
1796  // get the current character
1797  const int wc = static_cast<int>(str[current_wchar++]);
1798 
1799  // UTF-16 to UTF-8 encoding
1800  if (wc < 0x80)
1801  {
1802  utf8_bytes[0] = wc;
1803  utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
1804  }
1805  else if (wc <= 0x7FF)
1806  {
1807  utf8_bytes[0] = 0xC0 | ((wc >> 6));
1808  utf8_bytes[1] = 0x80 | (wc & 0x3F);
1809  utf8_bytes_filled = 2;
1810  }
1811  else if (0xD800 > wc or wc >= 0xE000)
1812  {
1813  utf8_bytes[0] = 0xE0 | ((wc >> 12));
1814  utf8_bytes[1] = 0x80 | ((wc >> 6) & 0x3F);
1815  utf8_bytes[2] = 0x80 | (wc & 0x3F);
1816  utf8_bytes_filled = 3;
1817  }
1818  else
1819  {
1820  if (current_wchar < str.size())
1821  {
1822  const int wc2 = static_cast<int>(str[current_wchar++]);
1823  const int charcode = 0x10000 + (((wc & 0x3FF) << 10) | (wc2 & 0x3FF));
1824  utf8_bytes[0] = 0xf0 | (charcode >> 18);
1825  utf8_bytes[1] = 0x80 | ((charcode >> 12) & 0x3F);
1826  utf8_bytes[2] = 0x80 | ((charcode >> 6) & 0x3F);
1827  utf8_bytes[3] = 0x80 | (charcode & 0x3F);
1828  utf8_bytes_filled = 4;
1829  }
1830  else
1831  {
1832  // unknown character
1833  ++current_wchar;
1834  utf8_bytes[0] = wc;
1835  utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
1836  }
1837  }
1838  }
1839  }
1840 
1841  void fill_buffer_utf32()
1842  {
1843  utf8_bytes_index = 0;
1844 
1845  if (current_wchar == str.size())
1846  {
1847  utf8_bytes[0] = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
1848  utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
1849  }
1850  else
1851  {
1852  // get the current character
1853  const int wc = static_cast<int>(str[current_wchar++]);
1854 
1855  // UTF-32 to UTF-8 encoding
1856  if (wc < 0x80)
1857  {
1858  utf8_bytes[0] = wc;
1859  utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
1860  }
1861  else if (wc <= 0x7FF)
1862  {
1863  utf8_bytes[0] = 0xC0 | ((wc >> 6) & 0x1F);
1864  utf8_bytes[1] = 0x80 | (wc & 0x3F);
1865  utf8_bytes_filled = 2;
1866  }
1867  else if (wc <= 0xFFFF)
1868  {
1869  utf8_bytes[0] = 0xE0 | ((wc >> 12) & 0x0F);
1870  utf8_bytes[1] = 0x80 | ((wc >> 6) & 0x3F);
1871  utf8_bytes[2] = 0x80 | (wc & 0x3F);
1872  utf8_bytes_filled = 3;
1873  }
1874  else if (wc <= 0x10FFFF)
1875  {
1876  utf8_bytes[0] = 0xF0 | ((wc >> 18 ) & 0x07);
1877  utf8_bytes[1] = 0x80 | ((wc >> 12) & 0x3F);
1878  utf8_bytes[2] = 0x80 | ((wc >> 6) & 0x3F);
1879  utf8_bytes[3] = 0x80 | (wc & 0x3F);
1880  utf8_bytes_filled = 4;
1881  }
1882  else
1883  {
1884  // unknown character
1885  utf8_bytes[0] = wc;
1886  utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
1887  }
1888  }
1889  }
1890 
1891  private:
1893  const WideStringType& str;
1894 
1896  std::size_t current_wchar = 0;
1897 
1899  std::array<std::char_traits<char>::int_type, 4> utf8_bytes = {{0, 0, 0, 0}};
1900 
1902  std::size_t utf8_bytes_index = 0;
1904  std::size_t utf8_bytes_filled = 0;
1905 
1907  std::char_traits<char>::int_type last_char = 0;
1909  bool next_unget = false;
1910 };
1911 
1912 class input_adapter
1913 {
1914  public:
1915  // native support
1916 
1918  input_adapter(std::istream& i)
1919  : ia(std::make_shared<input_stream_adapter>(i)) {}
1920 
1922  input_adapter(std::istream&& i)
1923  : ia(std::make_shared<input_stream_adapter>(i)) {}
1924 
1925  input_adapter(const std::wstring& ws)
1926  : ia(std::make_shared<wide_string_input_adapter<std::wstring>>(ws)) {}
1927 
1928  input_adapter(const std::u16string& ws)
1929  : ia(std::make_shared<wide_string_input_adapter<std::u16string>>(ws)) {}
1930 
1931  input_adapter(const std::u32string& ws)
1932  : ia(std::make_shared<wide_string_input_adapter<std::u32string>>(ws)) {}
1933 
1935  template<typename CharT,
1936  typename std::enable_if<
1937  std::is_pointer<CharT>::value and
1938  std::is_integral<typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type>::value and
1939  sizeof(typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type) == 1,
1940  int>::type = 0>
1941  input_adapter(CharT b, std::size_t l)
1942  : ia(std::make_shared<input_buffer_adapter>(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b), l)) {}
1943 
1944  // derived support
1945 
1947  template<typename CharT,
1948  typename std::enable_if<
1949  std::is_pointer<CharT>::value and
1950  std::is_integral<typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type>::value and
1951  sizeof(typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type) == 1,
1952  int>::type = 0>
1953  input_adapter(CharT b)
1954  : input_adapter(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b),
1955  std::strlen(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b))) {}
1956 
1958  template<class IteratorType,
1959  typename std::enable_if<
1960  std::is_same<typename std::iterator_traits<IteratorType>::iterator_category, std::random_access_iterator_tag>::value,
1961  int>::type = 0>
1962  input_adapter(IteratorType first, IteratorType last)
1963  {
1964  // assertion to check that the iterator range is indeed contiguous,
1965  // see http://stackoverflow.com/a/35008842/266378 for more discussion
1966  assert(std::accumulate(
1967  first, last, std::pair<bool, int>(true, 0),
1968  [&first](std::pair<bool, int> res, decltype(*first) val)
1969  {
1970  res.first &= (val == *(std::next(std::addressof(*first), res.second++)));
1971  return res;
1972  }).first);
1973 
1974  // assertion to check that each element is 1 byte long
1975  static_assert(
1976  sizeof(typename std::iterator_traits<IteratorType>::value_type) == 1,
1977  "each element in the iterator range must have the size of 1 byte");
1978 
1979  const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(std::distance(first, last));
1980  if (JSON_LIKELY(len > 0))
1981  {
1982  // there is at least one element: use the address of first
1983  ia = std::make_shared<input_buffer_adapter>(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(&(*first)), len);
1984  }
1985  else
1986  {
1987  // the address of first cannot be used: use nullptr
1988  ia = std::make_shared<input_buffer_adapter>(nullptr, len);
1989  }
1990  }
1991 
1993  template<class T, std::size_t N>
1994  input_adapter(T (&array)[N])
1995  : input_adapter(std::begin(array), std::end(array)) {}
1996 
1998  template<class ContiguousContainer, typename
1999  std::enable_if<not std::is_pointer<ContiguousContainer>::value and
2000  std::is_base_of<std::random_access_iterator_tag, typename std::iterator_traits<decltype(std::begin(std::declval<ContiguousContainer const>()))>::iterator_category>::value,
2001  int>::type = 0>
2002  input_adapter(const ContiguousContainer& c)
2003  : input_adapter(std::begin(c), std::end(c)) {}
2004 
2005  operator input_adapter_t()
2006  {
2007  return ia;
2008  }
2009 
2010  private:
2012  input_adapter_t ia = nullptr;
2013 };
2014 }
2015 }

2048 template<typename BasicJsonType>
2049 class lexer
2050 {
2051  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
2052  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
2053  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
2054  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
2055 
2056  public:
2058  enum class token_type
2059  {
2060  uninitialized,
2061  literal_true,
2062  literal_false,
2063  literal_null,
2064  value_string,
2065  value_unsigned,
2066  value_integer,
2067  value_float,
2068  begin_array,
2069  begin_object,
2070  end_array,
2071  end_object,
2072  name_separator,
2073  value_separator,
2074  parse_error,
2075  end_of_input,
2076  literal_or_value
2077  };
2078 
2080  static const char* token_type_name(const token_type t) noexcept
2081  {
2082  switch (t)
2083  {
2084  case token_type::uninitialized:
2085  return "<uninitialized>";
2086  case token_type::literal_true:
2087  return "true literal";
2088  case token_type::literal_false:
2089  return "false literal";
2090  case token_type::literal_null:
2091  return "null literal";
2092  case token_type::value_string:
2093  return "string literal";
2094  case lexer::token_type::value_unsigned:
2095  case lexer::token_type::value_integer:
2096  case lexer::token_type::value_float:
2097  return "number literal";
2098  case token_type::begin_array:
2099  return "'['";
2100  case token_type::begin_object:
2101  return "'{'";
2102  case token_type::end_array:
2103  return "']'";
2104  case token_type::end_object:
2105  return "'}'";
2106  case token_type::name_separator:
2107  return "':'";
2108  case token_type::value_separator:
2109  return "','";
2110  case token_type::parse_error:
2111  return "<parse error>";
2112  case token_type::end_of_input:
2113  return "end of input";
2114  case token_type::literal_or_value:
2115  return "'[', '{', or a literal";
2116  default: // catch non-enum values
2117  return "unknown token"; // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
2118  }
2119  }
2120 
2121  explicit lexer(detail::input_adapter_t adapter)
2122  : ia(std::move(adapter)), decimal_point_char(get_decimal_point()) {}
2123 
2124  // delete because of pointer members
2125  lexer(const lexer&) = delete;
2126  lexer& operator=(lexer&) = delete;
2127 
2128  private:
2130  // locales
2132 
2134  static char get_decimal_point() noexcept
2135  {
2136  const auto loc = localeconv();
2137  assert(loc != nullptr);
2138  return (loc->decimal_point == nullptr) ? '.' : *(loc->decimal_point);
2139  }
2140 
2142  // scan functions
2144 
2160  int get_codepoint()
2161  {
2162  // this function only makes sense after reading `\u`
2163  assert(current == 'u');
2164  int codepoint = 0;
2165 
2166  const auto factors = { 12, 8, 4, 0 };
2167  for (const auto factor : factors)
2168  {
2169  get();
2170 
2171  if (current >= '0' and current <= '9')
2172  {
2173  codepoint += ((current - 0x30) << factor);
2174  }
2175  else if (current >= 'A' and current <= 'F')
2176  {
2177  codepoint += ((current - 0x37) << factor);
2178  }
2179  else if (current >= 'a' and current <= 'f')
2180  {
2181  codepoint += ((current - 0x57) << factor);
2182  }
2183  else
2184  {
2185  return -1;
2186  }
2187  }
2188 
2189  assert(0x0000 <= codepoint and codepoint <= 0xFFFF);
2190  return codepoint;
2191  }
2192 
2208  bool next_byte_in_range(std::initializer_list<int> ranges)
2209  {
2210  assert(ranges.size() == 2 or ranges.size() == 4 or ranges.size() == 6);
2211  add(current);
2212 
2213  for (auto range = ranges.begin(); range != ranges.end(); ++range)
2214  {
2215  get();
2216  if (JSON_LIKELY(*range <= current and current <= *(++range)))
2217  {
2218  add(current);
2219  }
2220  else
2221  {
2222  error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
2223  return false;
2224  }
2225  }
2226 
2227  return true;
2228  }
2229 
2245  token_type scan_string()
2246  {
2247  // reset token_buffer (ignore opening quote)
2248  reset();
2249 
2250  // we entered the function by reading an open quote
2251  assert(current == '\"');
2252 
2253  while (true)
2254  {
2255  // get next character
2256  switch (get())
2257  {
2258  // end of file while parsing string
2259  case std::char_traits<char>::eof():
2260  {
2261  error_message = "invalid string: missing closing quote";
2262  return token_type::parse_error;
2263  }
2264 
2265  // closing quote
2266  case '\"':
2267  {
2268  return token_type::value_string;
2269  }
2270 
2271  // escapes
2272  case '\\':
2273  {
2274  switch (get())
2275  {
2276  // quotation mark
2277  case '\"':
2278  add('\"');
2279  break;
2280  // reverse solidus
2281  case '\\':
2282  add('\\');
2283  break;
2284  // solidus
2285  case '/':
2286  add('/');
2287  break;
2288  // backspace
2289  case 'b':
2290  add('\b');
2291  break;
2292  // form feed
2293  case 'f':
2294  add('\f');
2295  break;
2296  // line feed
2297  case 'n':
2298  add('\n');
2299  break;
2300  // carriage return
2301  case 'r':
2302  add('\r');
2303  break;
2304  // tab
2305  case 't':
2306  add('\t');
2307  break;
2308 
2309  // unicode escapes
2310  case 'u':
2311  {
2312  const int codepoint1 = get_codepoint();
2313  int codepoint = codepoint1; // start with codepoint1
2314 
2315  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(codepoint1 == -1))
2316  {
2317  error_message = "invalid string: '\\u' must be followed by 4 hex digits";
2318  return token_type::parse_error;
2319  }
2320 
2321  // check if code point is a high surrogate
2322  if (0xD800 <= codepoint1 and codepoint1 <= 0xDBFF)
2323  {
2324  // expect next \uxxxx entry
2325  if (JSON_LIKELY(get() == '\\' and get() == 'u'))
2326  {
2327  const int codepoint2 = get_codepoint();
2328 
2329  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(codepoint2 == -1))
2330  {
2331  error_message = "invalid string: '\\u' must be followed by 4 hex digits";
2332  return token_type::parse_error;
2333  }
2334 
2335  // check if codepoint2 is a low surrogate
2336  if (JSON_LIKELY(0xDC00 <= codepoint2 and codepoint2 <= 0xDFFF))
2337  {
2338  // overwrite codepoint
2339  codepoint =
2340  // high surrogate occupies the most significant 22 bits
2341  (codepoint1 << 10)
2342  // low surrogate occupies the least significant 15 bits
2343  + codepoint2
2344  // there is still the 0xD800, 0xDC00 and 0x10000 noise
2345  // in the result so we have to subtract with:
2346  // (0xD800 << 10) + DC00 - 0x10000 = 0x35FDC00
2347  - 0x35FDC00;
2348  }
2349  else
2350  {
2351  error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+DC00..U+DFFF must be followed by U+DC00..U+DFFF";
2352  return token_type::parse_error;
2353  }
2354  }
2355  else
2356  {
2357  error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+DC00..U+DFFF must be followed by U+DC00..U+DFFF";
2358  return token_type::parse_error;
2359  }
2360  }
2361  else
2362  {
2363  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(0xDC00 <= codepoint1 and codepoint1 <= 0xDFFF))
2364  {
2365  error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+DC00..U+DFFF must follow U+D800..U+DBFF";
2366  return token_type::parse_error;
2367  }
2368  }
2369 
2370  // result of the above calculation yields a proper codepoint
2371  assert(0x00 <= codepoint and codepoint <= 0x10FFFF);
2372 
2373  // translate codepoint into bytes
2374  if (codepoint < 0x80)
2375  {
2376  // 1-byte characters: 0xxxxxxx (ASCII)
2377  add(codepoint);
2378  }
2379  else if (codepoint <= 0x7FF)
2380  {
2381  // 2-byte characters: 110xxxxx 10xxxxxx
2382  add(0xC0 | (codepoint >> 6));
2383  add(0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F));
2384  }
2385  else if (codepoint <= 0xFFFF)
2386  {
2387  // 3-byte characters: 1110xxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
2388  add(0xE0 | (codepoint >> 12));
2389  add(0x80 | ((codepoint >> 6) & 0x3F));
2390  add(0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F));
2391  }
2392  else
2393  {
2394  // 4-byte characters: 11110xxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
2395  add(0xF0 | (codepoint >> 18));
2396  add(0x80 | ((codepoint >> 12) & 0x3F));
2397  add(0x80 | ((codepoint >> 6) & 0x3F));
2398  add(0x80 | (codepoint & 0x3F));
2399  }
2400 
2401  break;
2402  }
2403 
2404  // other characters after escape
2405  default:
2406  error_message = "invalid string: forbidden character after backslash";
2407  return token_type::parse_error;
2408  }
2409 
2410  break;
2411  }
2412 
2413  // invalid control characters
2414  case 0x00:
2415  case 0x01:
2416  case 0x02:
2417  case 0x03:
2418  case 0x04:
2419  case 0x05:
2420  case 0x06:
2421  case 0x07:
2422  case 0x08:
2423  case 0x09:
2424  case 0x0A:
2425  case 0x0B:
2426  case 0x0C:
2427  case 0x0D:
2428  case 0x0E:
2429  case 0x0F:
2430  case 0x10:
2431  case 0x11:
2432  case 0x12:
2433  case 0x13:
2434  case 0x14:
2435  case 0x15:
2436  case 0x16:
2437  case 0x17:
2438  case 0x18:
2439  case 0x19:
2440  case 0x1A:
2441  case 0x1B:
2442  case 0x1C:
2443  case 0x1D:
2444  case 0x1E:
2445  case 0x1F:
2446  {
2447  error_message = "invalid string: control character must be escaped";
2448  return token_type::parse_error;
2449  }
2450

2452  case 0x20:

2454  case 0x23:

2458  case 0x27:
2459  case 0x28:

2731  token_type scan_number()
2732  {
2733  // reset token_buffer to store the number's bytes
2734  reset();
2735 
2736  // the type of the parsed number; initially set to unsigned; will be
2737  // changed if minus sign, decimal point or exponent is read
2738  token_type number_type = token_type::value_unsigned;
2739 
2740  // state (init): we just found out we need to scan a number
2741  switch (current)
2742  {
2743  case '-':
2744  {
2745  add(current);
2746  goto scan_number_minus;
2747  }
2748 
2749  case '0':
2750  {
2751  add(current);
2752  goto scan_number_zero;
2753  }
2754 
2755  case '1':
2756  case '2':
2757  case '3':
2758  case '4':
2759  case '5':
2760  case '6':
2761  case '7':
2762  case '8':
2763  case '9':
2764  {
2765  add(current);
2766  goto scan_number_any1;
2767  }
2768 
2769  default:
2770  {
2771  // all other characters are rejected outside scan_number()
2772  assert(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
2773  }
2774  }
2775 
2776 scan_number_minus:
2777  // state: we just parsed a leading minus sign
2778  number_type = token_type::value_integer;
2779  switch (get())
2780  {
2781  case '0':
2782  {
2783  add(current);
2784  goto scan_number_zero;
2785  }
2786 
2787  case '1':
2788  case '2':
2789  case '3':
2790  case '4':
2791  case '5':
2792  case '6':
2793  case '7':
2794  case '8':
2795  case '9':
2796  {
2797  add(current);
2798  goto scan_number_any1;
2799  }
2800 
2801  default:
2802  {
2803  error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after '-'";
2804  return token_type::parse_error;
2805  }
2806  }
2807 
2808 scan_number_zero:
2809  // state: we just parse a zero (maybe with a leading minus sign)
2810  switch (get())
2811  {
2812  case '.':
2813  {
2814  add(decimal_point_char);
2815  goto scan_number_decimal1;
2816  }
2817 
2818  case 'e':
2819  case 'E':
2820  {
2821  add(current);
2822  goto scan_number_exponent;
2823  }
2824 
2825  default:
2826  goto scan_number_done;
2827  }
2828 
2829 scan_number_any1:
2830  // state: we just parsed a number 0-9 (maybe with a leading minus sign)
2831  switch (get())
2832  {
2833  case '0':
2834  case '1':
2835  case '2':
2836  case '3':
2837  case '4':
2838  case '5':
2839  case '6':
2840  case '7':
2841  case '8':
2842  case '9':
2843  {
2844  add(current);
2845  goto scan_number_any1;
2846  }
2847 
2848  case '.':
2849  {
2850  add(decimal_point_char);
2851  goto scan_number_decimal1;
2852  }
2853 
2854  case 'e':
2855  case 'E':
2856  {
2857  add(current);
2858  goto scan_number_exponent;
2859  }
2860 
2861  default:
2862  goto scan_number_done;
2863  }
2864 
2865 scan_number_decimal1:
2866  // state: we just parsed a decimal point
2867  number_type = token_type::value_float;
2868  switch (get())
2869  {
2870  case '0':
2871  case '1':
2872  case '2':
2873  case '3':
2874  case '4':
2875  case '5':
2876  case '6':
2877  case '7':
2878  case '8':
2879  case '9':
2880  {
2881  add(current);
2882  goto scan_number_decimal2;
2883  }
2884 
2885  default:
2886  {
2887  error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after '.'";
2888  return token_type::parse_error;
2889  }
2890  }
2891 
2892 scan_number_decimal2:
2893  // we just parsed at least one number after a decimal point
2894  switch (get())
2895  {
2896  case '0':
2897  case '1':
2898  case '2':
2899  case '3':
2900  case '4':
2901  case '5':
2902  case '6':
2903  case '7':
2904  case '8':
2905  case '9':

2907  add(current);
2908  goto scan_number_decimal2;
2909  }
2910 
2911  case 'e':
2912  case 'E':
2913  {
2914  add(current);
2915  goto scan_number_exponent;
2916  }
2917

2919  goto scan_number_done;
2920  }
2921 
2922 scan_number_exponent:
2923  // we just parsed an exponent
2924  number_type = token_type::value_float;
2925  switch (get())
2926  {
2927  case '+':
2928  case '-':
2929  {
2930  add(current);
2931  goto scan_number_sign;
2932  }
2933 
2934  case '0':
2935  case '1':
2936  case '2':
2937  case '3':
2938  case '4':
2939  case '5':
2940  case '6':
2941  case '7':
2942  case '8':
2943  case '9':
2944  {
2945  add(current);
2946  goto scan_number_any2;
2947  }
2948 
2949  default:
2950  {
2951  error_message =
2952  "invalid number; expected '+', '-', or digit after exponent";
2953  return token_type::parse_error;
2954  }
2955  }
2956 
2957 scan_number_sign:
2958  // we just parsed an exponent sign
2959  switch (get())
2960  {
2961  case '0':
2962  case '1':
2963  case '2':
2964  case '3':
2965  case '4':
2966  case '5':
2967  case '6':
2968  case '7':
2969  case '8':
2970  case '9':
2971  {
2972  add(current);
2973  goto scan_number_any2;
2974  }
2975 
2976  default:
2977  {
2978  error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after exponent sign";
2979  return token_type::parse_error;
2980  }
2981  }
2982 
2983 scan_number_any2:
2984  // we just parsed a number after the exponent or exponent sign
2985  switch (get())
2986  {
2987  case '0':
2988  case '1':
2989  case '2':
2990  case '3':
2991  case '4':
2992  case '5':
2993  case '6':
2994  case '7':
2995  case '8':
2996  case '9':
2997  {
2998  add(current);
2999  goto scan_number_any2;
3000  }
3001 
3002  default:
3003  goto scan_number_done;
3004  }
3005 
3006 scan_number_done:
3007  // unget the character after the number (we only read it to know that
3008  // we are done scanning a number)
3009  unget();
3010 
3011  char* endptr = nullptr;
3012  errno = 0;
3013 
3014  // try to parse integers first and fall back to floats
3015  if (number_type == token_type::value_unsigned)
3016  {
3017  const auto x = std::strtoull(token_buffer.data(), &endptr, 10);
3018 
3019  // we checked the number format before
3020  assert(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
3021 
3022  if (errno == 0)
3023  {
3024  value_unsigned = static_cast<number_unsigned_t>(x);
3025  if (value_unsigned == x)
3026  {
3027  return token_type::value_unsigned;
3028  }
3029  }
3030  }
3031  else if (number_type == token_type::value_integer)
3032  {
3033  const auto x = std::strtoll(token_buffer.data(), &endptr, 10);
3034 
3035  // we checked the number format before
3036  assert(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
3037 
3038  if (errno == 0)
3039  {
3040  value_integer = static_cast<number_integer_t>(x);
3041  if (value_integer == x)
3042  {
3043  return token_type::value_integer;
3044  }
3045  }
3046  }
3047 
3048  // this code is reached if we parse a floating-point number or if an
3049  // integer conversion above failed
3050  strtof(value_float, token_buffer.data(), &endptr);
3051 
3052  // we checked the number format before
3053  assert(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
3054 
3055  return token_type::value_float;
3056  }

3063  token_type scan_literal(const char* literal_text, const std::size_t length,
3064  token_type return_type)
3065  {
3066  assert(current == literal_text[0]);
3067  for (std::size_t i = 1; i < length; ++i)
3068  {
3069  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(get() != literal_text[i]))
3070  {
3071  error_message = "invalid literal";
3072  return token_type::parse_error;
3073  }
3074  }
3075  return return_type;
3076  }

3083  void reset() noexcept
3084  {
3085  token_buffer.clear();
3086  token_string.clear();
3087  token_string.push_back(std::char_traits<char>::to_char_type(current));
3088  }
3089 
3090  /*
3091  @brief get next character from the input
3092 
3093  This function provides the interface to the used input adapter. It does
3094  not throw in case the input reached EOF, but returns a
3095  `std::char_traits<char>::eof()` in that case. Stores the scanned characters
3096  for use in error messages.
3097 
3098  @return character read from the input
3099  */
3100  std::char_traits<char>::int_type get()
3101  {
3102  ++chars_read;
3103  current = ia->get_character();
3104  if (JSON_LIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char>::eof()))
3105  {
3106  token_string.push_back(std::char_traits<char>::to_char_type(current));
3107  }
3108  return current;
3109  }
3110 
3112  void unget()
3113  {
3114  --chars_read;
3115  if (JSON_LIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char>::eof()))
3116  {
3117  ia->unget_character();
3118  assert(token_string.size() != 0);
3119  token_string.pop_back();
3120  }
3121  }

3125  {
3126  token_buffer.push_back(std::char_traits<char>::to_char_type(c));
3127  }

3171  std::string get_token_string() const
3172  {
3173  // escape control characters
3174  std::string result;
3175  for (const auto c : token_string)
3176  {
3177  if ('\x00' <= c and c <= '\x1F')
3178  {
3179  // escape control characters
3180  std::stringstream ss;
3181  ss << "<U+" << std::setw(4) << std::uppercase << std::setfill('0')
3182  << std::hex << static_cast<int>(c) << ">";
3183  result += ss.str();
3184  }
3185  else
3186  {
3187  // add character as is
3188  result.push_back(c);
3189  }
3190  }
3191 
3192  return result;
3193  }
3194 
3196  constexpr const char* get_error_message() const noexcept
3197  {
3198  return error_message;
3199  }
3200 
3202  // actual scanner
3204 
3205  token_type scan()
3206  {
3207  // read next character and ignore whitespace
3208  do
3209  {
3210  get();
3211  }
3212  while (current == ' ' or current == '\t' or current == '\n' or current == '\r');
3213 
3214  switch (current)
3215  {
3216  // structural characters
3217  case '[':
3218  return token_type::begin_array;
3219  case ']':
3220  return token_type::end_array;
3221  case '{':
3222  return token_type::begin_object;
3223  case '}':
3224  return token_type::end_object;
3225  case ':':
3226  return token_type::name_separator;
3227  case ',':
3228  return token_type::value_separator;
3229 
3230  // literals
3231  case 't':
3232  return scan_literal("true", 4, token_type::literal_true);
3233  case 'f':
3234  return scan_literal("false", 5, token_type::literal_false);
3235  case 'n':
3236  return scan_literal("null", 4, token_type::literal_null);
3237 
3238  // string
3239  case '\"':
3240  return scan_string();
3241 
3242  // number
3243  case '-':
3244  case '0':
3245  case '1':
3246  case '2':
3247  case '3':
3248  case '4':
3249  case '5':
3250  case '6':
3251  case '7':
3252  case '8':
3253  case '9':
3254  return scan_number();
3255 
3256  // end of input (the null byte is needed when parsing from
3257  // string literals)
3258  case '\0':
3259  case std::char_traits<char>::eof():
3260  return token_type::end_of_input;
3261 
3262  // error
3263  default:
3264  error_message = "invalid literal";
3265  return token_type::parse_error;
3266  }
3267  }
3268 
3269  private:
3271  detail::input_adapter_t ia = nullptr;
3272 
3274  std::char_traits<char>::int_type current = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
3275 
3277  std::size_t chars_read = 0;
3278 
3280  std::vector<char> token_string {};
3281 
3283  string_t token_buffer {};
3284 
3286  const char* error_message = "";
3287 
3288  // number values
3289  number_integer_t value_integer = 0;
3290  number_unsigned_t value_unsigned = 0;
3291  number_float_t value_float = 0;
3292 
3294  const char decimal_point_char = '.';
3295 };
3296 }
3297 }

3300 
3301 
3302 #include <cassert> // assert
3303 #include <cmath> // isfinite
3304 #include <cstdint> // uint8_t
3305 #include <functional> // function
3306 #include <string> // string
3307 #include <utility> // move
3308 
3309 // #include <nlohmann/detail/exceptions.hpp>
3310 
3311 // #include <nlohmann/detail/macro_scope.hpp>
3312 
3313 // #include <nlohmann/detail/input/input_adapters.hpp>
3314 
3315 // #include <nlohmann/detail/input/lexer.hpp>
3316 
3317 // #include <nlohmann/detail/value_t.hpp>
3318 
3319 
3320 namespace nlohmann
3321 {
3322 namespace detail
3323 {
3325 // parser //
3327 
3333 template<typename BasicJsonType>
3334 class parser
3335 {
3336  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
3337  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
3338  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
3339  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
3340  using lexer_t = lexer<BasicJsonType>;
3341  using token_type = typename lexer_t::token_type;
3342 
3343  public:
3344  enum class parse_event_t : uint8_t
3345  {
3347  object_start,
3349  object_end,
3351  array_start,
3353  array_end,
3355  key,
3357  value
3358  };
3359 
3360  using parser_callback_t =
3361  std::function<bool(int depth, parse_event_t event, BasicJsonType& parsed)>;
3362 
3364  explicit parser(detail::input_adapter_t adapter,
3365  const parser_callback_t cb = nullptr,
3366  const bool allow_exceptions_ = true)
3367  : callback(cb), m_lexer(adapter), allow_exceptions(allow_exceptions_)
3368  {}
3369 
3380  void parse(const bool strict, BasicJsonType& result)
3381  {
3382  // read first token
3383  get_token();
3384 
3385  parse_internal(true, result);
3386  result.assert_invariant();
3387 
3388  // in strict mode, input must be completely read
3389  if (strict)
3390  {
3391  get_token();
3392  expect(token_type::end_of_input);
3393  }
3394 
3395  // in case of an error, return discarded value
3396  if (errored)
3397  {
3398  result = value_t::discarded;
3399  return;
3400  }
3401 
3402  // set top-level value to null if it was discarded by the callback
3403  // function
3404  if (result.is_discarded())
3405  {
3406  result = nullptr;
3407  }
3408  }
3409 
3416  bool accept(const bool strict = true)
3417  {
3418  // read first token
3419  get_token();
3420 
3421  if (not accept_internal())
3422  {
3423  return false;
3424  }
3425 
3426  // strict => last token must be EOF
3427  return not strict or (get_token() == token_type::end_of_input);
3428  }
3429 
3430  private:
3437  void parse_internal(bool keep, BasicJsonType& result)
3438  {
3439  // never parse after a parse error was detected
3440  assert(not errored);
3441 
3442  // start with a discarded value
3443  if (not result.is_discarded())
3444  {
3445  result.m_value.destroy(result.m_type);
3446  result.m_type = value_t::discarded;
3447  }
3448 
3449  switch (last_token)
3450  {
3451  case token_type::begin_object:
3452  {
3453  if (keep)
3454  {
3455  if (callback)
3456  {
3457  keep = callback(depth++, parse_event_t::object_start, result);
3458  }
3459 
3460  if (not callback or keep)
3461  {
3462  // explicitly set result to object to cope with {}
3463  result.m_type = value_t::object;
3464  result.m_value = value_t::object;
3465  }
3466  }
3467 
3468  // read next token
3469  get_token();
3470 
3471  // closing } -> we are done
3472  if (last_token == token_type::end_object)
3473  {
3474  if (keep and callback and not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::object_end, result))
3475  {
3476  result.m_value.destroy(result.m_type);
3477  result.m_type = value_t::discarded;
3478  }
3479  break;
3480  }
3481 
3482  // parse values
3483  string_t key;
3484  BasicJsonType value;
3485  while (true)
3486  {
3487  // store key
3488  if (not expect(token_type::value_string))
3489  {
3490  return;
3491  }
3492  key = m_lexer.move_string();
3493 
3494  bool keep_tag = false;
3495  if (keep)
3496  {
3497  if (callback)
3498  {
3499  BasicJsonType k(key);
3500  keep_tag = callback(depth, parse_event_t::key, k);
3501  }
3502  else
3503  {
3504  keep_tag = true;
3505  }
3506  }
3507 
3508  // parse separator (:)
3509  get_token();
3510  if (not expect(token_type::name_separator))
3511  {
3512  return;
3513  }
3514 
3515  // parse and add value
3516  get_token();
3517  value.m_value.destroy(value.m_type);
3518  value.m_type = value_t::discarded;
3519  parse_internal(keep, value);
3520 
3521  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(errored))
3522  {
3523  return;
3524  }
3525 
3526  if (keep and keep_tag and not value.is_discarded())
3527  {
3528  result.m_value.object->emplace(std::move(key), std::move(value));
3529  }
3530 
3531  // comma -> next value
3532  get_token();
3533  if (last_token == token_type::value_separator)
3534  {
3535  get_token();
3536  continue;
3537  }
3538 
3539  // closing }
3540  if (not expect(token_type::end_object))
3541  {
3542  return;
3543  }
3544  break;
3545  }
3546 
3547  if (keep and callback and not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::object_end, result))
3548  {
3549  result.m_value.destroy(result.m_type);
3550  result.m_type = value_t::discarded;
3551  }
3552  break;
3553  }
3554 
3555  case token_type::begin_array:
3556  {
3557  if (keep)
3558  {
3559  if (callback)
3560  {
3561  keep = callback(depth++, parse_event_t::array_start, result);
3562  }
3563 
3564  if (not callback or keep)
3565  {
3566  // explicitly set result to array to cope with []
3567  result.m_type = value_t::array;
3568  result.m_value = value_t::array;
3569  }
3570  }
3571 
3572  // read next token
3573  get_token();
3574 
3575  // closing ] -> we are done
3576  if (last_token == token_type::end_array)
3577  {
3578  if (callback and not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::array_end, result))
3579  {
3580  result.m_value.destroy(result.m_type);
3581  result.m_type = value_t::discarded;
3582  }
3583  break;
3584  }
3585 
3586  // parse values
3587  BasicJsonType value;
3588  while (true)
3589  {
3590  // parse value
3591  value.m_value.destroy(value.m_type);
3592  value.m_type = value_t::discarded;
3593  parse_internal(keep, value);
3594 
3595  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(errored))
3596  {
3597  return;
3598  }
3599 
3600  if (keep and not value.is_discarded())
3601  {
3602  result.m_value.array->push_back(std::move(value));
3603  }
3604 
3605  // comma -> next value
3606  get_token();
3607  if (last_token == token_type::value_separator)
3608  {
3609  get_token();
3610  continue;
3611  }
3612 
3613  // closing ]
3614  if (not expect(token_type::end_array))
3615  {
3616  return;
3617  }
3618  break;
3619  }
3620 
3621  if (keep and callback and not callback(--depth, parse_event_t::array_end, result))
3622  {
3623  result.m_value.destroy(result.m_type);
3624  result.m_type = value_t::discarded;
3625  }
3626  break;
3627  }
3628 
3629  case token_type::literal_null:
3630  {
3631  result.m_type = value_t::null;
3632  break;
3633  }
3634 
3635  case token_type::value_string:
3636  {
3637  result.m_type = value_t::string;
3638  result.m_value = m_lexer.move_string();
3639  break;
3640  }
3641 
3642  case token_type::literal_true:
3643  {
3644  result.m_type = value_t::boolean;
3645  result.m_value = true;
3646  break;
3647  }
3648 
3649  case token_type::literal_false:
3650  {
3651  result.m_type = value_t::boolean;
3652  result.m_value = false;
3653  break;
3654  }
3655 
3656  case token_type::value_unsigned:
3657  {
3658  result.m_type = value_t::number_unsigned;
3659  result.m_value = m_lexer.get_number_unsigned();
3660  break;
3661  }
3662 
3663  case token_type::value_integer:
3664  {
3665  result.m_type = value_t::number_integer;
3666  result.m_value = m_lexer.get_number_integer();
3667  break;
3668  }
3669 
3670  case token_type::value_float:
3671  {
3672  result.m_type = value_t::number_float;
3673  result.m_value = m_lexer.get_number_float();
3674 
3675  // throw in case of infinity or NAN
3676  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not std::isfinite(result.m_value.number_float)))
3677  {
3678  if (allow_exceptions)
3679  {
3680  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(406, "number overflow parsing '" +
3681  m_lexer.get_token_string() + "'"));
3682  }
3683  expect(token_type::uninitialized);
3684  }
3685  break;
3686  }
3687 
3688  case token_type::parse_error:
3689  {
3690  // using "uninitialized" to avoid "expected" message
3691  if (not expect(token_type::uninitialized))
3692  {
3693  return;
3694  }
3695  break; // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
3696  }
3697 
3698  default:
3699  {
3700  // the last token was unexpected; we expected a value
3701  if (not expect(token_type::literal_or_value))
3702  {
3703  return;
3704  }
3705  break; // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
3706  }
3707  }
3708 
3709  if (keep and callback and not callback(depth, parse_event_t::value, result))
3710  {
3711  result.m_value.destroy(result.m_type);
3712  result.m_type = value_t::discarded;
3713  }
3714  }
3715 
3726  bool accept_internal()
3727  {
3728  switch (last_token)
3729  {
3730  case token_type::begin_object:
3731  {
3732  // read next token
3733  get_token();
3734 
3735  // closing } -> we are done
3736  if (last_token == token_type::end_object)
3737  {
3738  return true;
3739  }
3740 
3741  // parse values
3742  while (true)
3743  {
3744  // parse key
3745  if (last_token != token_type::value_string)
3746  {
3747  return false;
3748  }
3749 
3750  // parse separator (:)
3751  get_token();
3752  if (last_token != token_type::name_separator)
3753  {
3754  return false;
3755  }
3756 
3757  // parse value
3758  get_token();
3759  if (not accept_internal())
3760  {
3761  return false;
3762  }
3763 
3764  // comma -> next value
3765  get_token();
3766  if (last_token == token_type::value_separator)
3767  {
3768  get_token();
3769  continue;
3770  }
3771 
3772  // closing }
3773  return (last_token == token_type::end_object);
3774  }
3775  }
3776 
3777  case token_type::begin_array:
3778  {
3779  // read next token
3780  get_token();
3781 
3782  // closing ] -> we are done
3783  if (last_token == token_type::end_array)
3784  {
3785  return true;
3786  }
3787 
3788  // parse values
3789  while (true)
3790  {
3791  // parse value
3792  if (not accept_internal())
3793  {
3794  return false;
3795  }
3796 
3797  // comma -> next value
3798  get_token();
3799  if (last_token == token_type::value_separator)
3800  {
3801  get_token();
3802  continue;
3803  }
3804 
3805  // closing ]
3806  return (last_token == token_type::end_array);
3807  }
3808  }
3809 
3810  case token_type::value_float:
3811  {
3812  // reject infinity or NAN
3813  return std::isfinite(m_lexer.get_number_float());
3814  }
3815 
3816  case token_type::literal_false:
3817  case token_type::literal_null:
3818  case token_type::literal_true:
3819  case token_type::value_integer:
3820  case token_type::value_string:
3821  case token_type::value_unsigned:
3822  return true;
3823 
3824  default: // the last token was unexpected
3825  return false;
3826  }
3827  }
3828 
3830  token_type get_token()
3831  {
3832  return (last_token = m_lexer.scan());
3833  }
3834 
3838  bool expect(token_type t)
3839  {
3840  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(t != last_token))
3841  {
3842  errored = true;
3843  expected = t;
3844  if (allow_exceptions)
3845  {
3846  throw_exception();
3847  }
3848  else
3849  {
3850  return false;
3851  }
3852  }
3853 
3854  return true;
3855  }
3856 
3857  [[noreturn]] void throw_exception() const
3858  {
3859  std::string error_msg = "syntax error - ";
3860  if (last_token == token_type::parse_error)
3861  {
3862  error_msg += std::string(m_lexer.get_error_message()) + "; last read: '" +
3863  m_lexer.get_token_string() + "'";
3864  }
3865  else
3866  {
3867  error_msg += "unexpected " + std::string(lexer_t::token_type_name(last_token));
3868  }
3869 
3870  if (expected != token_type::uninitialized)
3871  {
3872  error_msg += "; expected " + std::string(lexer_t::token_type_name(expected));
3873  }
3874 
3875  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), error_msg));
3876  }
3877 
3878  private:
3880  int depth = 0;
3882  const parser_callback_t callback = nullptr;
3884  token_type last_token = token_type::uninitialized;
3886  lexer_t m_lexer;
3888  bool errored = false;
3890  token_type expected = token_type::uninitialized;
3892  const bool allow_exceptions = true;
3893 };
3894 }
3895 }

3897 // #include <nlohmann/detail/iterators/primitive_iterator.hpp>
3898 
3899 
3900 #include <cstddef> // ptrdiff_t
3901 #include <limits> // numeric_limits
3902 
3903 namespace nlohmann
3904 {
3905 namespace detail
3906 {
3907 /*
3908 @brief an iterator for primitive JSON types
3909 
3910 This class models an iterator for primitive JSON types (boolean, number,
3911 string). It's only purpose is to allow the iterator/const_iterator classes
3912 to "iterate" over primitive values. Internally, the iterator is modeled by
3913 a `difference_type` variable. Value begin_value (`0`) models the begin,
3914 end_value (`1`) models past the end.
3915 */
3916 class primitive_iterator_t
3917 {
3918  private:
3919  using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
3920  static constexpr difference_type begin_value = 0;
3921  static constexpr difference_type end_value = begin_value + 1;
3922 
3924  difference_type m_it = (std::numeric_limits<std::ptrdiff_t>::min)();
3925 
3926  public:
3927  constexpr difference_type get_value() const noexcept
3928  {
3929  return m_it;
3930  }
3931 
3933  void set_begin() noexcept
3934  {
3935  m_it = begin_value;
3936  }
3937 
3939  void set_end() noexcept
3940  {
3941  m_it = end_value;
3942  }
3943 
3945  constexpr bool is_begin() const noexcept
3946  {
3947  return m_it == begin_value;
3948  }
3949 
3951  constexpr bool is_end() const noexcept
3952  {
3953  return m_it == end_value;
3954  }
3955 
3956  friend constexpr bool operator==(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept
3957  {
3958  return lhs.m_it == rhs.m_it;
3959  }
3960 
3961  friend constexpr bool operator<(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept
3962  {
3963  return lhs.m_it < rhs.m_it;
3964  }
3965 
3966  primitive_iterator_t operator+(difference_type n) noexcept
3967  {
3968  auto result = *this;
3969  result += n;
3970  return result;
3971  }
3972 
3973  friend constexpr difference_type operator-(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept
3974  {
3975  return lhs.m_it - rhs.m_it;
3976  }
3977 
3978  primitive_iterator_t& operator++() noexcept
3979  {
3980  ++m_it;
3981  return *this;
3982  }
3983 
3984  primitive_iterator_t const operator++(int) noexcept
3985  {
3986  auto result = *this;
3987  m_it++;
3988  return result;
3989  }
3990 
3991  primitive_iterator_t& operator--() noexcept
3992  {
3993  --m_it;
3994  return *this;
3995  }
3996 
3997  primitive_iterator_t const operator--(int) noexcept
3998  {
3999  auto result = *this;
4000  m_it--;
4001  return result;
4002  }
4003 
4004  primitive_iterator_t& operator+=(difference_type n) noexcept
4005  {
4006  m_it += n;
4007  return *this;
4008  }
4009 
4010  primitive_iterator_t& operator-=(difference_type n) noexcept
4011  {
4012  m_it -= n;
4013  return *this;
4014  }
4015 };
4016 }
4017 }

4105  static_assert(is_basic_json<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type>::value,
4106  "iter_impl only accepts (const) basic_json");

4140  explicit iter_impl(pointer object) noexcept : m_object(object)
4141  {
4142  assert(m_object != nullptr);
4143 
4144  switch (m_object->m_type)
4145  {
4146  case value_t::object:
4147  {
4148  m_it.object_iterator = typename object_t::iterator();
4149  break;
4150  }
4151 
4152  case value_t::array:
4153  {
4154  m_it.array_iterator = typename array_t::iterator();
4155  break;
4156  }
4157 
4158  default:
4159  {
4160  m_it.primitive_iterator = primitive_iterator_t();
4161  break;
4162  }
4163  }
4164  }

4192  m_it = other.m_it;

4206  {
4207  case value_t::object:
4208  {
4209  m_it.object_iterator = m_object->m_value.object->begin();
4210  break;
4211  }
4212 
4213  case value_t::array:
4214  {
4215  m_it.array_iterator = m_object->m_value.array->begin();
4216  break;
4217  }
4218 
4219  case value_t::null:
4220  {
4221  // set to end so begin()==end() is true: null is empty
4222  m_it.primitive_iterator.set_end();
4223  break;
4224  }
4225 
4226  default:

4228  m_it.primitive_iterator.set_begin();
4229  break;
4230  }
4231  }
4232  }

4242  switch (m_object->m_type)

4245  {
4246  m_it.object_iterator = m_object->m_value.object->end();
4247  break;
4248  }

4253  break;

4272

4274  {
4275  case value_t::object:
4276  {
4277  assert(m_it.object_iterator != m_object->m_value.object->end());
4278  return m_it.object_iterator->second;
4279  }
4280 
4281  case value_t::array:
4282  {
4283  assert(m_it.array_iterator != m_object->m_value.array->end());
4284  return *m_it.array_iterator;

4288  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
4289

4291  {
4292  if (JSON_LIKELY(m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin()))
4293  {
4294  return *m_object;
4295  }
4296 
4297  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
4298  }
4299  }
4300  }

4426  bool operator==(const iter_impl& other) const
4427  {
4428  // if objects are not the same, the comparison is undefined
4429  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(m_object != other.m_object))
4430  {
4431  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(212, "cannot compare iterators of different containers"));
4432  }
4433 
4434  assert(m_object != nullptr);
4435 
4436  switch (m_object->m_type)
4437  {
4438  case value_t::object:
4439  return (m_it.object_iterator == other.m_it.object_iterator);
4440 
4441  case value_t::array:
4442  return (m_it.array_iterator == other.m_it.array_iterator);
4443 
4444  default:
4445  return (m_it.primitive_iterator == other.m_it.primitive_iterator);
4446  }

4464  // if objects are not the same, the comparison is undefined

4466  {

4683 template<typename IteratorType> class iteration_proxy
4684 {
4685  private:
4687  class iteration_proxy_internal
4688  {
4689  private:
4691  IteratorType anchor;
4693  std::size_t array_index = 0;
4694 
4695  public:
4696  explicit iteration_proxy_internal(IteratorType it) noexcept : anchor(it) {}
4697 
4699  iteration_proxy_internal& operator*()
4700  {
4701  return *this;
4702  }
4703 
4705  iteration_proxy_internal& operator++()
4706  {
4707  ++anchor;
4708  ++array_index;
4709 
4710  return *this;
4711  }
4712 
4714  bool operator!=(const iteration_proxy_internal& o) const noexcept
4715  {
4716  return anchor != o.anchor;
4717  }
4718 
4720  std::string key() const
4721  {
4722  assert(anchor.m_object != nullptr);
4723 
4724  switch (anchor.m_object->type())
4725  {
4726  // use integer array index as key
4727  case value_t::array:
4728  return std::to_string(array_index);
4729 
4730  // use key from the object
4731  case value_t::object:
4732  return anchor.key();
4733 
4734  // use an empty key for all primitive types
4735  default:
4736  return "";
4737  }
4738  }
4739 
4741  typename IteratorType::reference value() const
4742  {
4743  return anchor.value();
4744  }
4745  };
4746 
4748  typename IteratorType::reference container;
4749 
4750  public:
4752  explicit iteration_proxy(typename IteratorType::reference cont) noexcept
4753  : container(cont) {}
4754 
4756  iteration_proxy_internal begin() noexcept
4757  {
4758  return iteration_proxy_internal(container.begin());
4759  }
4760 
4762  iteration_proxy_internal end() noexcept
4763  {
4764  return iteration_proxy_internal(container.end());
4765  }
4766 };
4767 }

4909 {
4910  virtual void write_character(CharType c) = 0;
4911  virtual void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) = 0;
4912  virtual ~output_adapter_protocol() = default;

4920 template<typename CharType>
4921 class output_vector_adapter : public output_adapter_protocol<CharType>
4922 {
4923  public:
4924  explicit output_vector_adapter(std::vector<CharType>& vec) : v(vec) {}
4925 
4926  void write_character(CharType c) override
4927  {
4928  v.push_back(c);
4929  }
4930 
4931  void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) override
4932  {
4933  std::copy(s, s + length, std::back_inserter(v));
4934  }
4935 
4936  private:

4938 };

4946

4948  {
4949  stream.put(c);
4950  }
4951 
4952  void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) override
4953  {
4954  stream.write(s, static_cast<std::streamsize>(length));
4955  }

5096  if (strict)
5097  {
5098  get();
5099  expect_eof();
5100  }
5101  return res;
5102  }
5103 
5114  BasicJsonType parse_ubjson(const bool strict)
5115  {
5116  const auto res = parse_ubjson_internal();
5117  if (strict)
5118  {
5119  get_ignore_noop();
5120  expect_eof();
5121  }
5122  return res;
5123  }
