5132  static constexpr bool little_endianess(int num = 1) noexcept
5133  {
5134  return (*reinterpret_cast<char*>(&num) == 1);
5135  }
5136 
5137  private:
5143  BasicJsonType parse_cbor_internal(const bool get_char = true)
5144  {
5145  switch (get_char ? get() : current)
5146  {
5147  // EOF
5148  case std::char_traits<char>::eof():
5149  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(110, chars_read, "unexpected end of input"));
5150 
5151  // Integer 0x00..0x17 (0..23)
5152  case 0x00:
5153  case 0x01:
5154  case 0x02:
5155  case 0x03:
5156  case 0x04:
5157  case 0x05:
5158  case 0x06:
5159  case 0x07:
5160  case 0x08:
5161  case 0x09:
5162  case 0x0A:
5163  case 0x0B:
5164  case 0x0C:
5165  case 0x0D:
5166  case 0x0E:
5167  case 0x0F:
5168  case 0x10:
5169  case 0x11:
5170  case 0x12:
5171  case 0x13:
5172  case 0x14:
5173  case 0x15:
5174  case 0x16:
5175  case 0x17:
5176  return static_cast<number_unsigned_t>(current);
5177 
5178  case 0x18: // Unsigned integer (one-byte uint8_t follows)
5179  return get_number<uint8_t>();
5180 
5181  case 0x19: // Unsigned integer (two-byte uint16_t follows)
5182  return get_number<uint16_t>();
5183 
5184  case 0x1A: // Unsigned integer (four-byte uint32_t follows)
5185  return get_number<uint32_t>();
5186 
5187  case 0x1B: // Unsigned integer (eight-byte uint64_t follows)
5188  return get_number<uint64_t>();
5189 
5190  // Negative integer -1-0x00..-1-0x17 (-1..-24)
5191  case 0x20:
5192  case 0x21:
5193  case 0x22:
5194  case 0x23:
5195  case 0x24:
5196  case 0x25:
5197  case 0x26:
5198  case 0x27:
5199  case 0x28:
5200  case 0x29:
5201  case 0x2A:
5202  case 0x2B:
5203  case 0x2C:
5204  case 0x2D:
5205  case 0x2E:
5206  case 0x2F:
5207  case 0x30:
5208  case 0x31:
5209  case 0x32:
5210  case 0x33:
5211  case 0x34:
5212  case 0x35:
5213  case 0x36:
5214  case 0x37:
5215  return static_cast<int8_t>(0x20 - 1 - current);
5216 
5217  case 0x38: // Negative integer (one-byte uint8_t follows)
5218  {
5219  return static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - get_number<uint8_t>();
5220  }
5221 
5222  case 0x39: // Negative integer -1-n (two-byte uint16_t follows)
5223  {
5224  return static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - get_number<uint16_t>();
5225  }
5226 
5227  case 0x3A: // Negative integer -1-n (four-byte uint32_t follows)
5228  {
5229  return static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - get_number<uint32_t>();
5230  }
5231 
5232  case 0x3B: // Negative integer -1-n (eight-byte uint64_t follows)
5233  {
5234  return static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) -
5235  static_cast<number_integer_t>(get_number<uint64_t>());
5236  }
5237 
5238  // UTF-8 string (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
5239  case 0x60:
5240  case 0x61:
5241  case 0x62:
5242  case 0x63:
5243  case 0x64:
5244  case 0x65:
5245  case 0x66:
5246  case 0x67:
5247  case 0x68:
5248  case 0x69:
5249  case 0x6A:
5250  case 0x6B:
5251  case 0x6C:
5252  case 0x6D:
5253  case 0x6E:
5254  case 0x6F:
5255  case 0x70:
5256  case 0x71:
5257  case 0x72:
5258  case 0x73:
5259  case 0x74:
5260  case 0x75:
5261  case 0x76:
5262  case 0x77:
5263  case 0x78: // UTF-8 string (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
5264  case 0x79: // UTF-8 string (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
5265  case 0x7A: // UTF-8 string (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
5266  case 0x7B: // UTF-8 string (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
5267  case 0x7F: // UTF-8 string (indefinite length)
5268  {
5269  return get_cbor_string();
5270  }
5271 
5272  // array (0x00..0x17 data items follow)
5273  case 0x80:
5274  case 0x81:
5275  case 0x82:
5276  case 0x83:
5277  case 0x84:
5278  case 0x85:
5279  case 0x86:
5280  case 0x87:
5281  case 0x88:
5282  case 0x89:
5283  case 0x8A:
5284  case 0x8B:
5285  case 0x8C:
5286  case 0x8D:
5287  case 0x8E:
5288  case 0x8F:
5289  case 0x90:
5290  case 0x91:
5291  case 0x92:
5292  case 0x93:
5293  case 0x94:
5294  case 0x95:
5295  case 0x96:
5296  case 0x97:
5297  {
5298  return get_cbor_array(current & 0x1F);
5299  }
5300 
5301  case 0x98: // array (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
5302  {
5303  return get_cbor_array(get_number<uint8_t>());
5304  }
5305 
5306  case 0x99: // array (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
5307  {
5308  return get_cbor_array(get_number<uint16_t>());
5309  }
5310 
5311  case 0x9A: // array (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
5312  {
5313  return get_cbor_array(get_number<uint32_t>());
5314  }
5315 
5316  case 0x9B: // array (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
5317  {
5318  return get_cbor_array(get_number<uint64_t>());
5319  }
5320 
5321  case 0x9F: // array (indefinite length)
5322  {
5323  BasicJsonType result = value_t::array;
5324  while (get() != 0xFF)
5325  {
5326  result.push_back(parse_cbor_internal(false));
5327  }
5328  return result;
5329  }
5330 
5331  // map (0x00..0x17 pairs of data items follow)
5332  case 0xA0:
5333  case 0xA1:
5334  case 0xA2:
5335  case 0xA3:
5336  case 0xA4:
5337  case 0xA5:
5338  case 0xA6:
5339  case 0xA7:
5340  case 0xA8:
5341  case 0xA9:
5342  case 0xAA:
5343  case 0xAB:
5344  case 0xAC:
5345  case 0xAD:
5346  case 0xAE:
5347  case 0xAF:
5348  case 0xB0:
5349  case 0xB1:
5350  case 0xB2:
5351  case 0xB3:
5352  case 0xB4:
5353  case 0xB5:
5354  case 0xB6:
5355  case 0xB7:
5356  {
5357  return get_cbor_object(current & 0x1F);
5358  }
5359 
5360  case 0xB8: // map (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
5361  {
5362  return get_cbor_object(get_number<uint8_t>());
5363  }
5364 
5365  case 0xB9: // map (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
5366  {
5367  return get_cbor_object(get_number<uint16_t>());
5368  }
5369 
5370  case 0xBA: // map (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
5371  {
5372  return get_cbor_object(get_number<uint32_t>());
5373  }
5374 
5375  case 0xBB: // map (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
5376  {
5377  return get_cbor_object(get_number<uint64_t>());
5378  }
5379 
5380  case 0xBF: // map (indefinite length)
5381  {
5382  BasicJsonType result = value_t::object;
5383  while (get() != 0xFF)
5384  {
5385  auto key = get_cbor_string();
5386  result[key] = parse_cbor_internal();
5387  }
5388  return result;
5389  }
5390 
5391  case 0xF4: // false
5392  {
5393  return false;
5394  }
5395 
5396  case 0xF5: // true
5397  {
5398  return true;
5399  }
5400 
5401  case 0xF6: // null
5402  {
5403  return value_t::null;
5404  }
5405 
5406  case 0xF9: // Half-Precision Float (two-byte IEEE 754)
5407  {
5408  const int byte1 = get();
5409  unexpect_eof();
5410  const int byte2 = get();
5411  unexpect_eof();
5412 
5413  // code from RFC 7049, Appendix D, Figure 3:
5414  // As half-precision floating-point numbers were only added
5415  // to IEEE 754 in 2008, today's programming platforms often
5416  // still only have limited support for them. It is very
5417  // easy to include at least decoding support for them even
5418  // without such support. An example of a small decoder for
5419  // half-precision floating-point numbers in the C language
5420  // is shown in Fig. 3.
5421  const int half = (byte1 << 8) + byte2;
5422  const int exp = (half >> 10) & 0x1F;
5423  const int mant = half & 0x3FF;
5424  double val;
5425  if (exp == 0)
5426  {
5427  val = std::ldexp(mant, -24);
5428  }
5429  else if (exp != 31)
5430  {
5431  val = std::ldexp(mant + 1024, exp - 25);
5432  }
5433  else
5434  {
5435  val = (mant == 0) ? std::numeric_limits<double>::infinity()
5436  : std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
5437  }
5438  return (half & 0x8000) != 0 ? -val : val;
5439  }
5440 
5441  case 0xFA: // Single-Precision Float (four-byte IEEE 754)
5442  {
5443  return get_number<float>();
5444  }
5445 
5446  case 0xFB: // Double-Precision Float (eight-byte IEEE 754)
5447  {
5448  return get_number<double>();
5449  }
5450 
5451  default: // anything else (0xFF is handled inside the other types)
5452  {
5453  std::stringstream ss;
5454  ss << std::setw(2) << std::uppercase << std::setfill('0') << std::hex << current;
5455  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(112, chars_read, "error reading CBOR; last byte: 0x" + ss.str()));
5456  }
5457  }
5458  }

5804  int get()

5813  int get_ignore_noop()
5814  {
5815  do
5816  {
5817  get();
5818  }
5819  while (current == 'N');
5820 
5821  return current;
5822  }
5823 
5824  /*
5825  @brief read a number from the input
5826 
5827  @tparam NumberType the type of the number
5828 
5829  @return number of type @a NumberType
5830 
5831  @note This function needs to respect the system's endianess, because
5832  bytes in CBOR and MessagePack are stored in network order (big
5833  endian) and therefore need reordering on little endian systems.
5834 
5835  @throw parse_error.110 if input has less than `sizeof(NumberType)` bytes
5836  */
5837  template<typename NumberType> NumberType get_number()
5838  {
5839  // step 1: read input into array with system's byte order
5840  std::array<uint8_t, sizeof(NumberType)> vec;
5841  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < sizeof(NumberType); ++i)
5842  {
5843  get();
5844  unexpect_eof();
5845 
5846  // reverse byte order prior to conversion if necessary
5847  if (is_little_endian)
5848  {
5849  vec[sizeof(NumberType) - i - 1] = static_cast<uint8_t>(current);
5850  }
5851  else
5852  {
5853  vec[i] = static_cast<uint8_t>(current); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
5854  }
5855  }
5856 
5857  // step 2: convert array into number of type T and return
5858  NumberType result;
5859  std::memcpy(&result, vec.data(), sizeof(NumberType));
5860  return result;
5861  }
5862 
5876  template<typename NumberType>
5877  string_t get_string(const NumberType len)
5878  {
5879  string_t result;
5880  std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(result), len, [this]()
5881  {
5882  get();
5883  unexpect_eof();
5884  return static_cast<char>(current);
5885  });
5886  return result;
5887  }
5888 
5901  string_t get_cbor_string()
5902  {
5903  unexpect_eof();
5904 
5905  switch (current)
5906  {
5907  // UTF-8 string (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
5908  case 0x60:
5909  case 0x61:
5910  case 0x62:
5911  case 0x63:
5912  case 0x64:
5913  case 0x65:
5914  case 0x66:
5915  case 0x67:
5916  case 0x68:
5917  case 0x69:
5918  case 0x6A:
5919  case 0x6B:
5920  case 0x6C:
5921  case 0x6D:
5922  case 0x6E:
5923  case 0x6F:
5924  case 0x70:
5925  case 0x71:
5926  case 0x72:
5927  case 0x73:
5928  case 0x74:
5929  case 0x75:
5930  case 0x76:
5931  case 0x77:
5932  {
5933  return get_string(current & 0x1F);
5934  }
5935 
5936  case 0x78: // UTF-8 string (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
5937  {
5938  return get_string(get_number<uint8_t>());
5939  }
5940 
5941  case 0x79: // UTF-8 string (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
5942  {
5943  return get_string(get_number<uint16_t>());
5944  }
5945 
5946  case 0x7A: // UTF-8 string (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
5947  {
5948  return get_string(get_number<uint32_t>());
5949  }
5950 
5951  case 0x7B: // UTF-8 string (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
5952  {
5953  return get_string(get_number<uint64_t>());
5954  }
5955 
5956  case 0x7F: // UTF-8 string (indefinite length)
5957  {
5958  string_t result;
5959  while (get() != 0xFF)
5960  {
5961  result.append(get_cbor_string());
5962  }
5963  return result;
5964  }
5965 
5966  default:
5967  {
5968  std::stringstream ss;
5969  ss << std::setw(2) << std::uppercase << std::setfill('0') << std::hex << current;
5970  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(113, chars_read, "expected a CBOR string; last byte: 0x" + ss.str()));
5971  }
5972  }
5973  }
5974 
5975  template<typename NumberType>
5976  BasicJsonType get_cbor_array(const NumberType len)
5977  {
5978  BasicJsonType result = value_t::array;
5979  std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(*result.m_value.array), len, [this]()
5980  {
5981  return parse_cbor_internal();
5982  });
5983  return result;
5984  }
5985 
5986  template<typename NumberType>
5987  BasicJsonType get_cbor_object(const NumberType len)
5988  {
5989  BasicJsonType result = value_t::object;
5990  std::generate_n(std::inserter(*result.m_value.object,
5991  result.m_value.object->end()),
5992  len, [this]()
5993  {
5994  get();
5995  auto key = get_cbor_string();
5996  auto val = parse_cbor_internal();
5997  return std::make_pair(std::move(key), std::move(val));
5998  });
5999  return result;
6000  }

6013  string_t get_msgpack_string()
6014  {
6015  unexpect_eof();
6016 
6017  switch (current)
6018  {
6019  // fixstr
6020  case 0xA0:
6021  case 0xA1:
6022  case 0xA2:
6023  case 0xA3:
6024  case 0xA4:
6025  case 0xA5:
6026  case 0xA6:
6027  case 0xA7:
6028  case 0xA8:
6029  case 0xA9:
6030  case 0xAA:
6031  case 0xAB:
6032  case 0xAC:
6033  case 0xAD:
6034  case 0xAE:
6035  case 0xAF:
6036  case 0xB0:
6037  case 0xB1:
6038  case 0xB2:
6039  case 0xB3:
6040  case 0xB4:
6041  case 0xB5:
6042  case 0xB6:
6043  case 0xB7:
6044  case 0xB8:
6045  case 0xB9:
6046  case 0xBA:
6047  case 0xBB:
6048  case 0xBC:
6049  case 0xBD:
6050  case 0xBE:
6051  case 0xBF:

6054  }

6057  {

6059  }
6060

6062  {

6075  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(113, chars_read,
6076  "expected a MessagePack string; last byte: 0x" + ss.str()));
6077  }
6078  }
6079  }

6107 
6124  string_t get_ubjson_string(const bool get_char = true)
6125  {
6126  if (get_char)
6127  {
6128  get(); // TODO: may we ignore N here?
6129  }
6130 
6131  unexpect_eof();
6132 
6133  switch (current)
6134  {
6135  case 'U':
6136  return get_string(get_number<uint8_t>());
6137  case 'i':
6138  return get_string(get_number<int8_t>());
6139  case 'I':
6140  return get_string(get_number<int16_t>());
6141  case 'l':
6142  return get_string(get_number<int32_t>());
6143  case 'L':
6144  return get_string(get_number<int64_t>());
6145  default:
6146  std::stringstream ss;
6147  ss << std::setw(2) << std::uppercase << std::setfill('0') << std::hex << current;
6148  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(113, chars_read,
6149  "expected a UBJSON string; last byte: 0x" + ss.str()));
6150  }
6151  }
6152 
6161  std::pair<std::size_t, int> get_ubjson_size_type()
6162  {
6163  std::size_t sz = string_t::npos;
6164  int tc = 0;
6165 
6166  get_ignore_noop();
6167 
6168  if (current == '$')
6169  {
6170  tc = get(); // must not ignore 'N', because 'N' maybe the type
6171  unexpect_eof();
6172 
6173  get_ignore_noop();
6174  if (current != '#')
6175  {
6176  std::stringstream ss;
6177  ss << std::setw(2) << std::uppercase << std::setfill('0') << std::hex << current;
6178  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(112, chars_read,
6179  "expected '#' after UBJSON type information; last byte: 0x" + ss.str()));
6180  }
6181  sz = parse_ubjson_internal();
6182  }
6183  else if (current == '#')
6184  {
6185  sz = parse_ubjson_internal();
6186  }
6187 
6188  return std::make_pair(sz, tc);
6189  }
6190 
6191  BasicJsonType get_ubjson_value(const int prefix)
6192  {
6193  switch (prefix)
6194  {
6195  case std::char_traits<char>::eof(): // EOF
6196  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(110, chars_read, "unexpected end of input"));
6197 
6198  case 'T': // true
6199  return true;
6200  case 'F': // false
6201  return false;
6202 
6203  case 'Z': // null
6204  return nullptr;
6205 
6206  case 'U':
6207  return get_number<uint8_t>();
6208  case 'i':
6209  return get_number<int8_t>();
6210  case 'I':
6211  return get_number<int16_t>();
6212  case 'l':
6213  return get_number<int32_t>();
6214  case 'L':
6215  return get_number<int64_t>();
6216  case 'd':
6217  return get_number<float>();
6218  case 'D':
6219  return get_number<double>();
6220 
6221  case 'C': // char
6222  {
6223  get();
6224  unexpect_eof();
6225  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(current > 127))
6226  {
6227  std::stringstream ss;
6228  ss << std::setw(2) << std::uppercase << std::setfill('0') << std::hex << current;
6229  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(113, chars_read,
6230  "byte after 'C' must be in range 0x00..0x7F; last byte: 0x" + ss.str()));
6231  }
6232  return string_t(1, static_cast<char>(current));
6233  }
6234 
6235  case 'S': // string
6236  return get_ubjson_string();
6237 
6238  case '[': // array
6239  return get_ubjson_array();
6240 
6241  case '{': // object
6242  return get_ubjson_object();
6243 
6244  default: // anything else
6245  std::stringstream ss;
6246  ss << std::setw(2) << std::uppercase << std::setfill('0') << std::hex << current;
6247  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(112, chars_read,
6248  "error reading UBJSON; last byte: 0x" + ss.str()));
6249  }
6250  }
6251 
6252  BasicJsonType get_ubjson_array()
6253  {
6254  BasicJsonType result = value_t::array;
6255  const auto size_and_type = get_ubjson_size_type();
6256 
6257  if (size_and_type.first != string_t::npos)
6258  {
6259  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(size_and_type.first > result.max_size()))
6260  {
6261  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(408,
6262  "excessive array size: " + std::to_string(size_and_type.first)));
6263  }
6264 
6265  if (size_and_type.second != 0)
6266  {
6267  if (size_and_type.second != 'N')
6268  {
6269  std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(*result.m_value.array),
6270  size_and_type.first, [this, size_and_type]()
6271  {
6272  return get_ubjson_value(size_and_type.second);
6273  });
6274  }
6275  }
6276  else
6277  {
6278  std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(*result.m_value.array),
6279  size_and_type.first, [this]()
6280  {
6281  return parse_ubjson_internal();
6282  });
6283  }
6284  }
6285  else
6286  {
6287  while (current != ']')
6288  {
6289  result.push_back(parse_ubjson_internal(false));
6290  get_ignore_noop();
6291  }
6292  }
6293 
6294  return result;
6295  }
6296 
6297  BasicJsonType get_ubjson_object()
6298  {
6299  BasicJsonType result = value_t::object;
6300  const auto size_and_type = get_ubjson_size_type();
6301 
6302  if (size_and_type.first != string_t::npos)
6303  {
6304  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(size_and_type.first > result.max_size()))
6305  {
6306  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(408,
6307  "excessive object size: " + std::to_string(size_and_type.first)));
6308  }
6309 
6310  if (size_and_type.second != 0)
6311  {
6312  std::generate_n(std::inserter(*result.m_value.object,
6313  result.m_value.object->end()),
6314  size_and_type.first, [this, size_and_type]()
6315  {
6316  auto key = get_ubjson_string();
6317  auto val = get_ubjson_value(size_and_type.second);
6318  return std::make_pair(std::move(key), std::move(val));
6319  });
6320  }
6321  else
6322  {
6323  std::generate_n(std::inserter(*result.m_value.object,
6324  result.m_value.object->end()),
6325  size_and_type.first, [this]()
6326  {
6327  auto key = get_ubjson_string();
6328  auto val = parse_ubjson_internal();
6329  return std::make_pair(std::move(key), std::move(val));
6330  });
6331  }
6332  }
6333  else
6334  {
6335  while (current != '}')
6336  {
6337  auto key = get_ubjson_string(false);
6338  result[std::move(key)] = parse_ubjson_internal();
6339  get_ignore_noop();
6340  }
6341  }
6342 
6343  return result;
6344  }
6345 
6350  void expect_eof() const
6351  {
6352  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char>::eof()))
6353  {
6354  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(110, chars_read, "expected end of input"));
6355  }
6356  }
6357 
6362  void unexpect_eof() const
6363  {
6364  if (JSON_UNLIKELY(current == std::char_traits<char>::eof()))
6365  {
6366  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(110, chars_read, "unexpected end of input"));
6367  }
6368  }
6369 
6370  private:
6372  input_adapter_t ia = nullptr;
6373 
6375  int current = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
6376 
6378  std::size_t chars_read = 0;
6379 
6381  const bool is_little_endian = little_endianess();
6382 };
6383 }
6384 }

6389 #include <algorithm> // reverse
6390 #include <array> // array
6391 #include <cstdint> // uint8_t, uint16_t, uint32_t, uint64_t
6392 #include <cstring> // memcpy
6393 #include <limits> // numeric_limits
6394 
6395 // #include <nlohmann/detail/input/binary_reader.hpp>
6396 
6397 // #include <nlohmann/detail/output/output_adapters.hpp>
6398 
6399 
6400 namespace nlohmann
6401 {
6402 namespace detail
6403 {
6405 // binary writer //
6407 
6411 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename CharType>
6412 class binary_writer
6413 {
6414  public:
6420  explicit binary_writer(output_adapter_t<CharType> adapter) : oa(adapter)
6421  {
6422  assert(oa);
6423  }
6424 
6428  void write_cbor(const BasicJsonType& j)
6429  {
6430  switch (j.type())
6431  {
6432  case value_t::null:
6433  {
6434  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xF6));
6435  break;
6436  }
6437 
6438  case value_t::boolean:
6439  {
6440  oa->write_character(j.m_value.boolean
6441  ? static_cast<CharType>(0xF5)
6442  : static_cast<CharType>(0xF4));
6443  break;
6444  }
6445 
6446  case value_t::number_integer:
6447  {
6448  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= 0)
6449  {
6450  // CBOR does not differentiate between positive signed
6451  // integers and unsigned integers. Therefore, we used the
6452  // code from the value_t::number_unsigned case here.
6453  if (j.m_value.number_integer <= 0x17)
6454  {
6455  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6456  }
6457  else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)())
6458  {
6459  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x18));
6460  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6461  }
6462  else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)())
6463  {
6464  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x19));
6465  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6466  }
6467  else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)())
6468  {
6469  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x1A));
6470  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6471  }
6472  else
6473  {
6474  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x1B));
6475  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6476  }
6477  }
6478  else
6479  {
6480  // The conversions below encode the sign in the first
6481  // byte, and the value is converted to a positive number.
6482  const auto positive_number = -1 - j.m_value.number_integer;
6483  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= -24)
6484  {
6485  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(0x20 + positive_number));
6486  }
6487  else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)())
6488  {
6489  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x38));
6490  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(positive_number));
6491  }
6492  else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)())
6493  {
6494  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x39));
6495  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(positive_number));
6496  }
6497  else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)())
6498  {
6499  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x3A));
6500  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(positive_number));
6501  }
6502  else
6503  {
6504  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x3B));
6505  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(positive_number));
6506  }
6507  }
6508  break;
6509  }
6510 
6511  case value_t::number_unsigned:
6512  {
6513  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= 0x17)
6514  {
6515  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
6516  }
6517  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)())
6518  {
6519  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x18));
6520  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
6521  }
6522  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)())
6523  {
6524  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x19));
6525  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
6526  }
6527  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)())
6528  {
6529  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x1A));
6530  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
6531  }
6532  else
6533  {
6534  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x1B));
6535  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
6536  }
6537  break;
6538  }
6539 
6540  case value_t::number_float:
6541  {
6542  oa->write_character(get_cbor_float_prefix(j.m_value.number_float));
6543  write_number(j.m_value.number_float);
6544  break;
6545  }
6546 
6547  case value_t::string:
6548  {
6549  // step 1: write control byte and the string length
6550  const auto N = j.m_value.string->size();
6551  if (N <= 0x17)
6552  {
6553  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(0x60 + N));
6554  }
6555  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)())
6556  {
6557  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x78));
6558  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(N));
6559  }
6560  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)())
6561  {
6562  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x79));
6563  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(N));
6564  }
6565  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)())
6566  {
6567  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x7A));
6568  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(N));
6569  }
6570  // LCOV_EXCL_START
6571  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max)())
6572  {
6573  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x7B));
6574  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(N));
6575  }
6576  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
6577 
6578  // step 2: write the string
6579  oa->write_characters(
6580  reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.string->c_str()),
6581  j.m_value.string->size());
6582  break;
6583  }
6584 
6585  case value_t::array:
6586  {
6587  // step 1: write control byte and the array size
6588  const auto N = j.m_value.array->size();
6589  if (N <= 0x17)
6590  {
6591  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(0x80 + N));
6592  }
6593  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)())
6594  {
6595  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x98));
6596  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(N));
6597  }
6598  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)())
6599  {
6600  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x99));
6601  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(N));
6602  }
6603  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)())
6604  {
6605  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x9A));
6606  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(N));
6607  }
6608  // LCOV_EXCL_START
6609  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max)())
6610  {
6611  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0x9B));
6612  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(N));
6613  }
6614  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
6615 
6616  // step 2: write each element
6617  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array)
6618  {
6619  write_cbor(el);
6620  }
6621  break;
6622  }
6623 
6624  case value_t::object:
6625  {
6626  // step 1: write control byte and the object size
6627  const auto N = j.m_value.object->size();
6628  if (N <= 0x17)
6629  {
6630  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(0xA0 + N));
6631  }
6632  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)())
6633  {
6634  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xB8));
6635  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(N));
6636  }
6637  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)())
6638  {
6639  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xB9));
6640  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(N));
6641  }
6642  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)())
6643  {
6644  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xBA));
6645  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(N));
6646  }
6647  // LCOV_EXCL_START
6648  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max)())
6649  {
6650  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xBB));
6651  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(N));
6652  }
6653  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
6654 
6655  // step 2: write each element
6656  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object)
6657  {
6658  write_cbor(el.first);
6659  write_cbor(el.second);
6660  }
6661  break;
6662  }
6663 
6664  default:
6665  break;
6666  }
6667  }
6668 
6672  void write_msgpack(const BasicJsonType& j)
6673  {
6674  switch (j.type())
6675  {
6676  case value_t::null: // nil
6677  {
6678  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xC0));
6679  break;
6680  }
6681 
6682  case value_t::boolean: // true and false
6683  {
6684  oa->write_character(j.m_value.boolean
6685  ? static_cast<CharType>(0xC3)
6686  : static_cast<CharType>(0xC2));
6687  break;
6688  }
6689 
6690  case value_t::number_integer:
6691  {
6692  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= 0)
6693  {
6694  // MessagePack does not differentiate between positive
6695  // signed integers and unsigned integers. Therefore, we used
6696  // the code from the value_t::number_unsigned case here.
6697  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned < 128)
6698  {
6699  // positive fixnum
6700  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6701  }
6702  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)())
6703  {
6704  // uint 8
6705  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xCC));
6706  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6707  }
6708  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)())
6709  {
6710  // uint 16
6711  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xCD));
6712  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6713  }
6714  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)())
6715  {
6716  // uint 32
6717  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xCE));
6718  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6719  }
6720  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max)())
6721  {
6722  // uint 64
6723  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xCF));
6724  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6725  }
6726  }
6727  else
6728  {
6729  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= -32)
6730  {
6731  // negative fixnum
6732  write_number(static_cast<int8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6733  }
6734  else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::min)() and
6735  j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::max)())
6736  {
6737  // int 8
6738  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xD0));
6739  write_number(static_cast<int8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6740  }
6741  else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::min)() and
6742  j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::max)())
6743  {
6744  // int 16
6745  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xD1));
6746  write_number(static_cast<int16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6747  }
6748  else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min)() and
6749  j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max)())
6750  {
6751  // int 32
6752  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xD2));
6753  write_number(static_cast<int32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6754  }
6755  else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min)() and
6756  j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max)())
6757  {
6758  // int 64
6759  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xD3));
6760  write_number(static_cast<int64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6761  }
6762  }
6763  break;
6764  }
6765 
6766  case value_t::number_unsigned:
6767  {
6768  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned < 128)
6769  {
6770  // positive fixnum
6771  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6772  }
6773  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)())
6774  {
6775  // uint 8
6776  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xCC));
6777  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6778  }
6779  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)())
6780  {
6781  // uint 16
6782  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xCD));
6783  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6784  }
6785  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)())
6786  {
6787  // uint 32
6788  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xCE));
6789  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6790  }
6791  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint64_t>::max)())
6792  {
6793  // uint 64
6794  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xCF));
6795  write_number(static_cast<uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
6796  }
6797  break;
6798  }
6799 
6800  case value_t::number_float:
6801  {
6802  oa->write_character(get_msgpack_float_prefix(j.m_value.number_float));
6803  write_number(j.m_value.number_float);
6804  break;
6805  }
6806 
6807  case value_t::string:
6808  {
6809  // step 1: write control byte and the string length
6810  const auto N = j.m_value.string->size();
6811  if (N <= 31)
6812  {
6813  // fixstr
6814  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(0xA0 | N));
6815  }
6816  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)())
6817  {
6818  // str 8
6819  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xD9));
6820  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(N));
6821  }
6822  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)())
6823  {
6824  // str 16
6825  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xDA));
6826  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(N));
6827  }
6828  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)())
6829  {
6830  // str 32
6831  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xDB));
6832  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(N));
6833  }
6834 
6835  // step 2: write the string
6836  oa->write_characters(
6837  reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.string->c_str()),
6838  j.m_value.string->size());
6839  break;
6840  }
6841 
6842  case value_t::array:
6843  {
6844  // step 1: write control byte and the array size
6845  const auto N = j.m_value.array->size();
6846  if (N <= 15)
6847  {
6848  // fixarray
6849  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(0x90 | N));
6850  }
6851  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)())
6852  {
6853  // array 16
6854  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xDC));
6855  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(N));
6856  }
6857  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)())
6858  {
6859  // array 32
6860  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xDD));
6861  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(N));
6862  }
6863 
6864  // step 2: write each element
6865  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array)
6866  {
6867  write_msgpack(el);
6868  }
6869  break;
6870  }
6871 
6872  case value_t::object:
6873  {
6874  // step 1: write control byte and the object size
6875  const auto N = j.m_value.object->size();
6876  if (N <= 15)
6877  {
6878  // fixmap
6879  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(0x80 | (N & 0xF)));
6880  }
6881  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max)())
6882  {
6883  // map 16
6884  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xDE));
6885  write_number(static_cast<uint16_t>(N));
6886  }
6887  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max)())
6888  {
6889  // map 32
6890  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(0xDF));
6891  write_number(static_cast<uint32_t>(N));
6892  }
6893 
6894  // step 2: write each element
6895  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object)
6896  {
6897  write_msgpack(el.first);
6898  write_msgpack(el.second);
6899  }
6900  break;
6901  }
6902 
6903  default:
6904  break;
6905  }
6906  }
6907 
6914  void write_ubjson(const BasicJsonType& j, const bool use_count,
6915  const bool use_type, const bool add_prefix = true)
6916  {
6917  switch (j.type())
6918  {
6919  case value_t::null:
6920  {
6921  if (add_prefix)
6922  {
6923  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('Z'));
6924  }
6925  break;
6926  }
6927 
6928  case value_t::boolean:
6929  {
6930  if (add_prefix)
6931  oa->write_character(j.m_value.boolean
6932  ? static_cast<CharType>('T')
6933  : static_cast<CharType>('F'));
6934  break;
6935  }
6936 
6937  case value_t::number_integer:
6938  {
6939  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.number_integer, add_prefix);
6940  break;
6941  }
6942 
6943  case value_t::number_unsigned:
6944  {
6945  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.number_unsigned, add_prefix);
6946  break;
6947  }
6948 
6949  case value_t::number_float:
6950  {
6951  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.number_float, add_prefix);
6952  break;
6953  }
6954 
6955  case value_t::string:
6956  {
6957  if (add_prefix)
6958  {
6959  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('S'));
6960  }
6961  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.string->size(), true);
6962  oa->write_characters(
6963  reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.string->c_str()),
6964  j.m_value.string->size());
6965  break;
6966  }
6967 
6968  case value_t::array:
6969  {
6970  if (add_prefix)
6971  {
6972  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('['));
6973  }
6974 
6975  bool prefix_required = true;
6976  if (use_type and not j.m_value.array->empty())
6977  {
6978  assert(use_count);
6979  const CharType first_prefix = ubjson_prefix(j.front());
6980  const bool same_prefix = std::all_of(j.begin() + 1, j.end(),
6981  [this, first_prefix](const BasicJsonType & v)
6982  {
6983  return ubjson_prefix(v) == first_prefix;
6984  });
6985 
6986  if (same_prefix)
6987  {
6988  prefix_required = false;
6989  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('$'));
6990  oa->write_character(first_prefix);
6991  }
6992  }
6993 
6994  if (use_count)
6995  {
6996  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('#'));
6997  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.array->size(), true);
6998  }
6999 
7000  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array)
7001  {
7002  write_ubjson(el, use_count, use_type, prefix_required);
7003  }
7004 
7005  if (not use_count)
7006  {
7007  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>(']'));
7008  }
7009 
7010  break;
7011  }
7012 
7013  case value_t::object:
7014  {
7015  if (add_prefix)
7016  {
7017  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('{'));
7018  }
7019 
7020  bool prefix_required = true;
7021  if (use_type and not j.m_value.object->empty())
7022  {
7023  assert(use_count);
7024  const CharType first_prefix = ubjson_prefix(j.front());
7025  const bool same_prefix = std::all_of(j.begin(), j.end(),
7026  [this, first_prefix](const BasicJsonType & v)
7027  {
7028  return ubjson_prefix(v) == first_prefix;
7029  });
7030 
7031  if (same_prefix)
7032  {
7033  prefix_required = false;
7034  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('$'));
7035  oa->write_character(first_prefix);
7036  }
7037  }
7038 
7039  if (use_count)
7040  {
7041  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('#'));
7042  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.object->size(), true);
7043  }
7044 
7045  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object)
7046  {
7047  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(el.first.size(), true);
7048  oa->write_characters(
7049  reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(el.first.c_str()),
7050  el.first.size());
7051  write_ubjson(el.second, use_count, use_type, prefix_required);
7052  }
7053 
7054  if (not use_count)
7055  {
7056  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('}'));
7057  }
7058 
7059  break;
7060  }
7061 
7062  default:
7063  break;
7064  }
7065  }
7066 
7067  private:
7068  /*
7069  @brief write a number to output input
7070 
7071  @param[in] n number of type @a NumberType
7072  @tparam NumberType the type of the number
7073 
7074  @note This function needs to respect the system's endianess, because bytes
7075  in CBOR, MessagePack, and UBJSON are stored in network order (big
7076  endian) and therefore need reordering on little endian systems.
7077  */
7078  template<typename NumberType>
7079  void write_number(const NumberType n)
7080  {
7081  // step 1: write number to array of length NumberType
7082  std::array<CharType, sizeof(NumberType)> vec;
7083  std::memcpy(vec.data(), &n, sizeof(NumberType));
7084 
7085  // step 2: write array to output (with possible reordering)
7086  if (is_little_endian)
7087  {
7088  // reverse byte order prior to conversion if necessary
7089  std::reverse(vec.begin(), vec.end());
7090  }
7091 
7092  oa->write_characters(vec.data(), sizeof(NumberType));
7093  }
7094 
7095  // UBJSON: write number (floating point)
7096  template<typename NumberType, typename std::enable_if<
7097  std::is_floating_point<NumberType>::value, int>::type = 0>
7098  void write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(const NumberType n,
7099  const bool add_prefix)
7100  {
7101  if (add_prefix)
7102  {
7103  oa->write_character(get_ubjson_float_prefix(n));
7104  }
7105  write_number(n);
7106  }
7107 
7108  // UBJSON: write number (unsigned integer)
7109  template<typename NumberType, typename std::enable_if<
7110  std::is_unsigned<NumberType>::value, int>::type = 0>
7111  void write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(const NumberType n,
7112  const bool add_prefix)
7113  {
7114  if (n <= static_cast<uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::max)()))
7115  {
7116  if (add_prefix)
7117  {
7118  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('i')); // int8
7119  }
7120  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(n));
7121  }
7122  else if (n <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)())
7123  {
7124  if (add_prefix)
7125  {
7126  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('U')); // uint8
7127  }
7128  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(n));
7129  }
7130  else if (n <= static_cast<uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::max)()))
7131  {
7132  if (add_prefix)
7133  {
7134  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('I')); // int16
7135  }
7136  write_number(static_cast<int16_t>(n));
7137  }
7138  else if (n <= static_cast<uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max)()))
7139  {
7140  if (add_prefix)
7141  {
7142  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('l')); // int32
7143  }
7144  write_number(static_cast<int32_t>(n));
7145  }
7146  else if (n <= static_cast<uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max)()))
7147  {
7148  if (add_prefix)
7149  {
7150  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('L')); // int64
7151  }
7152  write_number(static_cast<int64_t>(n));
7153  }
7154  else
7155  {
7156  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(407, "number overflow serializing " + std::to_string(n)));
7157  }
7158  }
7159 
7160  // UBJSON: write number (signed integer)
7161  template<typename NumberType, typename std::enable_if<
7162  std::is_signed<NumberType>::value and
7163  not std::is_floating_point<NumberType>::value, int>::type = 0>
7164  void write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(const NumberType n,
7165  const bool add_prefix)
7166  {
7167  if ((std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::min)() <= n and n <= (std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::max)())
7168  {
7169  if (add_prefix)
7170  {
7171  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('i')); // int8
7172  }
7173  write_number(static_cast<int8_t>(n));
7174  }
7175  else if (static_cast<int64_t>((std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::min)()) <= n and n <= static_cast<int64_t>((std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)()))
7176  {
7177  if (add_prefix)
7178  {
7179  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('U')); // uint8
7180  }
7181  write_number(static_cast<uint8_t>(n));
7182  }
7183  else if ((std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::min)() <= n and n <= (std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::max)())
7184  {
7185  if (add_prefix)
7186  {
7187  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('I')); // int16
7188  }
7189  write_number(static_cast<int16_t>(n));
7190  }
7191  else if ((std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min)() <= n and n <= (std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max)())
7192  {
7193  if (add_prefix)
7194  {
7195  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('l')); // int32
7196  }
7197  write_number(static_cast<int32_t>(n));
7198  }
7199  else if ((std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min)() <= n and n <= (std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max)())
7200  {
7201  if (add_prefix)
7202  {
7203  oa->write_character(static_cast<CharType>('L')); // int64
7204  }
7205  write_number(static_cast<int64_t>(n));
7206  }
7207  // LCOV_EXCL_START
7208  else
7209  {
7210  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(407, "number overflow serializing " + std::to_string(n)));
7211  }
7212  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
7213  }
7214 
7224  CharType ubjson_prefix(const BasicJsonType& j) const noexcept
7225  {
7226  switch (j.type())
7227  {
7228  case value_t::null:
7229  return 'Z';
7230 
7231  case value_t::boolean:
7232  return j.m_value.boolean ? 'T' : 'F';
7233 
7234  case value_t::number_integer:
7235  {
7236  if ((std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::min)() <= j.m_value.number_integer and j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::max)())
7237  {
7238  return 'i';
7239  }
7240  else if ((std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::min)() <= j.m_value.number_integer and j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)())
7241  {
7242  return 'U';
7243  }
7244  else if ((std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::min)() <= j.m_value.number_integer and j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::max)())
7245  {
7246  return 'I';
7247  }
7248  else if ((std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min)() <= j.m_value.number_integer and j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max)())
7249  {
7250  return 'l';
7251  }
7252  else // no check and assume int64_t (see note above)
7253  {
7254  return 'L';
7255  }
7256  }
7257 
7258  case value_t::number_unsigned:
7259  {
7260  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<int8_t>::max)())
7261  {
7262  return 'i';
7263  }
7264  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<uint8_t>::max)())
7265  {
7266  return 'U';
7267  }
7268  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<int16_t>::max)())
7269  {
7270  return 'I';
7271  }
7272  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max)())
7273  {
7274  return 'l';
7275  }
7276  else // no check and assume int64_t (see note above)
7277  {
7278  return 'L';
7279  }
7280  }
7281 
7282  case value_t::number_float:
7283  return get_ubjson_float_prefix(j.m_value.number_float);
7284 
7285  case value_t::string:
7286  return 'S';
7287 
7288  case value_t::array:
7289  return '[';
7290 
7291  case value_t::object:
7292  return '{';
7293 
7294  default: // discarded values
7295  return 'N';
7296  }
7297  }
7298 
7299  static constexpr CharType get_cbor_float_prefix(float)
7300  {
7301  return static_cast<CharType>(0xFA); // Single-Precision Float
7302  }
7303 
7304  static constexpr CharType get_cbor_float_prefix(double)
7305  {
7306  return static_cast<CharType>(0xFB); // Double-Precision Float
7307  }
7308 
7309  static constexpr CharType get_msgpack_float_prefix(float)
7310  {
7311  return static_cast<CharType>(0xCA); // float 32
7312  }
7313 
7314  static constexpr CharType get_msgpack_float_prefix(double)
7315  {
7316  return static_cast<CharType>(0xCB); // float 64
7317  }
7318 
7319  static constexpr CharType get_ubjson_float_prefix(float)
7320  {
7321  return 'd'; // float 32
7322  }
7323 
7324  static constexpr CharType get_ubjson_float_prefix(double)
7325  {
7326  return 'D'; // float 64
7327  }
7328 
7329  private:
7331  const bool is_little_endian = binary_reader<BasicJsonType>::little_endianess();
7332 
7334  output_adapter_t<CharType> oa = nullptr;
7335 };
7336 }
7337 }

7396 template <typename Target, typename Source>
7397 Target reinterpret_bits(const Source source)
7398 {
7399  static_assert(sizeof(Target) == sizeof(Source), "size mismatch");
7400 
7401  Target target;
7402  std::memcpy(&target, &source, sizeof(Source));
7403  return target;
7404 }
7405 
7406 struct diyfp // f * 2^e
7407 {
7408  static constexpr int kPrecision = 64; // = q
7409 
7410  uint64_t f;
7411  int e;
7412 
7413  constexpr diyfp() noexcept : f(0), e(0) {}
7414  constexpr diyfp(uint64_t f_, int e_) noexcept : f(f_), e(e_) {}
7415 
7420  static diyfp sub(const diyfp& x, const diyfp& y) noexcept
7421  {
7422  assert(x.e == y.e);
7423  assert(x.f >= y.f);
7424 
7425  return diyfp(x.f - y.f, x.e);
7426  }
7427 
7432  static diyfp mul(const diyfp& x, const diyfp& y) noexcept
7433  {
7434  static_assert(kPrecision == 64, "internal error");
7435 
7436  // Computes:
7437  // f = round((x.f * y.f) / 2^q)
7438  // e = x.e + y.e + q
7439 
7440  // Emulate the 64-bit * 64-bit multiplication:
7441  //
7442  // p = u * v
7443  // = (u_lo + 2^32 u_hi) (v_lo + 2^32 v_hi)
7444  // = (u_lo v_lo ) + 2^32 ((u_lo v_hi ) + (u_hi v_lo )) + 2^64 (u_hi v_hi )
7445  // = (p0 ) + 2^32 ((p1 ) + (p2 )) + 2^64 (p3 )
7446  // = (p0_lo + 2^32 p0_hi) + 2^32 ((p1_lo + 2^32 p1_hi) + (p2_lo + 2^32 p2_hi)) + 2^64 (p3 )
7447  // = (p0_lo ) + 2^32 (p0_hi + p1_lo + p2_lo ) + 2^64 (p1_hi + p2_hi + p3)
7448  // = (p0_lo ) + 2^32 (Q ) + 2^64 (H )
7449  // = (p0_lo ) + 2^32 (Q_lo + 2^32 Q_hi ) + 2^64 (H )
7450  //
7451  // (Since Q might be larger than 2^32 - 1)
7452  //
7453  // = (p0_lo + 2^32 Q_lo) + 2^64 (Q_hi + H)
7454  //
7455  // (Q_hi + H does not overflow a 64-bit int)
7456  //
7457  // = p_lo + 2^64 p_hi
7458 
7459  const uint64_t u_lo = x.f & 0xFFFFFFFF;
7460  const uint64_t u_hi = x.f >> 32;
7461  const uint64_t v_lo = y.f & 0xFFFFFFFF;
7462  const uint64_t v_hi = y.f >> 32;
7463 
7464  const uint64_t p0 = u_lo * v_lo;
7465  const uint64_t p1 = u_lo * v_hi;
7466  const uint64_t p2 = u_hi * v_lo;
7467  const uint64_t p3 = u_hi * v_hi;
7468 
7469  const uint64_t p0_hi = p0 >> 32;
7470  const uint64_t p1_lo = p1 & 0xFFFFFFFF;
7471  const uint64_t p1_hi = p1 >> 32;
7472  const uint64_t p2_lo = p2 & 0xFFFFFFFF;
7473  const uint64_t p2_hi = p2 >> 32;
7474 
7475  uint64_t Q = p0_hi + p1_lo + p2_lo;
7476 
7477  // The full product might now be computed as
7478  //
7479  // p_hi = p3 + p2_hi + p1_hi + (Q >> 32)
7480  // p_lo = p0_lo + (Q << 32)
7481  //
7482  // But in this particular case here, the full p_lo is not required.
7483  // Effectively we only need to add the highest bit in p_lo to p_hi (and
7484  // Q_hi + 1 does not overflow).
7485 
7486  Q += uint64_t{1} << (64 - 32 - 1); // round, ties up
7487 
7488  const uint64_t h = p3 + p2_hi + p1_hi + (Q >> 32);
7489 
7490  return diyfp(h, x.e + y.e + 64);
7491  }
7492 
7497  static diyfp normalize(diyfp x) noexcept
7498  {
7499  assert(x.f != 0);
7500 
7501  while ((x.f >> 63) == 0)
7502  {
7503  x.f <<= 1;
7504  x.e--;
7505  }
7506 
7507  return x;
7508  }
7509 
7514  static diyfp normalize_to(const diyfp& x, const int target_exponent) noexcept
7515  {
7516  const int delta = x.e - target_exponent;
7517 
7518  assert(delta >= 0);
7519  assert(((x.f << delta) >> delta) == x.f);
7520 
7521  return diyfp(x.f << delta, target_exponent);
7522  }
7523 };
7524 
7525 struct boundaries
7526 {
7527  diyfp w;
7528  diyfp minus;
7529  diyfp plus;
7530 };
7531 
7538 template <typename FloatType>
7539 boundaries compute_boundaries(FloatType value)
7540 {
7541  assert(std::isfinite(value));
7542  assert(value > 0);
7543 
7544  // Convert the IEEE representation into a diyfp.
7545  //
7546  // If v is denormal:
7547  // value = 0.F * 2^(1 - bias) = ( F) * 2^(1 - bias - (p-1))
7548  // If v is normalized:
7549  // value = 1.F * 2^(E - bias) = (2^(p-1) + F) * 2^(E - bias - (p-1))
7550 
7551  static_assert(std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::is_iec559,
7552  "internal error: dtoa_short requires an IEEE-754 floating-point implementation");
7553 
7554  constexpr int kPrecision = std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::digits; // = p (includes the hidden bit)
7555  constexpr int kBias = std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::max_exponent - 1 + (kPrecision - 1);
7556  constexpr int kMinExp = 1 - kBias;
7557  constexpr uint64_t kHiddenBit = uint64_t{1} << (kPrecision - 1); // = 2^(p-1)
7558 
7559  using bits_type = typename std::conditional< kPrecision == 24, uint32_t, uint64_t >::type;
7560 
7561  const uint64_t bits = reinterpret_bits<bits_type>(value);
7562  const uint64_t E = bits >> (kPrecision - 1);
7563  const uint64_t F = bits & (kHiddenBit - 1);
7564 
7565  const bool is_denormal = (E == 0);
7566  const diyfp v = is_denormal
7567  ? diyfp(F, kMinExp)
7568  : diyfp(F + kHiddenBit, static_cast<int>(E) - kBias);
7569 
7570  // Compute the boundaries m- and m+ of the floating-point value
7571  // v = f * 2^e.
7572  //
7573  // Determine v- and v+, the floating-point predecessor and successor if v,
7574  // respectively.
7575  //
7576  // v- = v - 2^e if f != 2^(p-1) or e == e_min (A)
7577  // = v - 2^(e-1) if f == 2^(p-1) and e > e_min (B)
7578  //
7579  // v+ = v + 2^e
7580  //
7581  // Let m- = (v- + v) / 2 and m+ = (v + v+) / 2. All real numbers _strictly_
7582  // between m- and m+ round to v, regardless of how the input rounding
7583  // algorithm breaks ties.
7584  //
7585  // ---+-------------+-------------+-------------+-------------+--- (A)
7586  // v- m- v m+ v+
7587  //
7588  // -----------------+------+------+-------------+-------------+--- (B)
7589  // v- m- v m+ v+
7590 
7591  const bool lower_boundary_is_closer = (F == 0 and E > 1);
7592  const diyfp m_plus = diyfp(2 * v.f + 1, v.e - 1);
7593  const diyfp m_minus = lower_boundary_is_closer
7594  ? diyfp(4 * v.f - 1, v.e - 2) // (B)
7595  : diyfp(2 * v.f - 1, v.e - 1); // (A)
7596 
7597  // Determine the normalized w+ = m+.
7598  const diyfp w_plus = diyfp::normalize(m_plus);
7599 
7600  // Determine w- = m- such that e_(w-) = e_(w+).
7601  const diyfp w_minus = diyfp::normalize_to(m_minus, w_plus.e);
7602 
7603  return {diyfp::normalize(v), w_minus, w_plus};
7604 }
7605 
7606 // Given normalized diyfp w, Grisu needs to find a (normalized) cached
7607 // power-of-ten c, such that the exponent of the product c * w = f * 2^e lies
7608 // within a certain range [alpha, gamma] (Definition 3.2 from [1])
7609 //
7610 // alpha <= e = e_c + e_w + q <= gamma
7611 //
7612 // or
7613 //
7614 // f_c * f_w * 2^alpha <= f_c 2^(e_c) * f_w 2^(e_w) * 2^q
7615 // <= f_c * f_w * 2^gamma
7616 //
7617 // Since c and w are normalized, i.e. 2^(q-1) <= f < 2^q, this implies
7618 //
7619 // 2^(q-1) * 2^(q-1) * 2^alpha <= c * w * 2^q < 2^q * 2^q * 2^gamma
7620 //
7621 // or
7622 //
7623 // 2^(q - 2 + alpha) <= c * w < 2^(q + gamma)
7624 //
7625 // The choice of (alpha,gamma) determines the size of the table and the form of
7626 // the digit generation procedure. Using (alpha,gamma)=(-60,-32) works out well
7627 // in practice:
7628 //
7629 // The idea is to cut the number c * w = f * 2^e into two parts, which can be
7630 // processed independently: An integral part p1, and a fractional part p2:
7631 //
7632 // f * 2^e = ( (f div 2^-e) * 2^-e + (f mod 2^-e) ) * 2^e
7633 // = (f div 2^-e) + (f mod 2^-e) * 2^e
7634 // = p1 + p2 * 2^e
7635 //
7636 // The conversion of p1 into decimal form requires a series of divisions and
7637 // modulos by (a power of) 10. These operations are faster for 32-bit than for
7638 // 64-bit integers, so p1 should ideally fit into a 32-bit integer. This can be
7639 // achieved by choosing
7640 //
7641 // -e >= 32 or e <= -32 := gamma
7642 //
7643 // In order to convert the fractional part
7644 //
7645 // p2 * 2^e = p2 / 2^-e = d[-1] / 10^1 + d[-2] / 10^2 + ...
7646 //
7647 // into decimal form, the fraction is repeatedly multiplied by 10 and the digits
7648 // d[-i] are extracted in order:
7649 //
7650 // (10 * p2) div 2^-e = d[-1]
7651 // (10 * p2) mod 2^-e = d[-2] / 10^1 + ...
7652 //
7653 // The multiplication by 10 must not overflow. It is sufficient to choose
7654 //
7655 // 10 * p2 < 16 * p2 = 2^4 * p2 <= 2^64.
7656 //
7657 // Since p2 = f mod 2^-e < 2^-e,
7658 //
7659 // -e <= 60 or e >= -60 := alpha
7660 
7661 constexpr int kAlpha = -60;
7662 constexpr int kGamma = -32;
7663 
7664 struct cached_power // c = f * 2^e ~= 10^k
7665 {
7666  uint64_t f;
7667  int e;
7668  int k;
7669 };
7670 
7678 inline cached_power get_cached_power_for_binary_exponent(int e)
7679 {
7680  // Now
7681  //
7682  // alpha <= e_c + e + q <= gamma (1)
7683  // ==> f_c * 2^alpha <= c * 2^e * 2^q
7684  //
7685  // and since the c's are normalized, 2^(q-1) <= f_c,
7686  //
7687  // ==> 2^(q - 1 + alpha) <= c * 2^(e + q)
7688  // ==> 2^(alpha - e - 1) <= c
7689  //
7690  // If c were an exakt power of ten, i.e. c = 10^k, one may determine k as
7691  //
7692  // k = ceil( log_10( 2^(alpha - e - 1) ) )
7693  // = ceil( (alpha - e - 1) * log_10(2) )
7694  //
7695  // From the paper:
7696  // "In theory the result of the procedure could be wrong since c is rounded,
7697  // and the computation itself is approximated [...]. In practice, however,
7698  // this simple function is sufficient."
7699  //
7700  // For IEEE double precision floating-point numbers converted into
7701  // normalized diyfp's w = f * 2^e, with q = 64,
7702  //
7703  // e >= -1022 (min IEEE exponent)
7704  // -52 (p - 1)
7705  // -52 (p - 1, possibly normalize denormal IEEE numbers)
7706  // -11 (normalize the diyfp)
7707  // = -1137
7708  //
7709  // and
7710  //
7711  // e <= +1023 (max IEEE exponent)
7712  // -52 (p - 1)
7713  // -11 (normalize the diyfp)
7714  // = 960
7715  //
7716  // This binary exponent range [-1137,960] results in a decimal exponent
7717  // range [-307,324]. One does not need to store a cached power for each
7718  // k in this range. For each such k it suffices to find a cached power
7719  // such that the exponent of the product lies in [alpha,gamma].
7720  // This implies that the difference of the decimal exponents of adjacent
7721  // table entries must be less than or equal to
7722  //
7723  // floor( (gamma - alpha) * log_10(2) ) = 8.
7724  //
7725  // (A smaller distance gamma-alpha would require a larger table.)
7726 
7727  // NB:
7728  // Actually this function returns c, such that -60 <= e_c + e + 64 <= -34.
7729 
7730  constexpr int kCachedPowersSize = 79;
7731  constexpr int kCachedPowersMinDecExp = -300;
7732  constexpr int kCachedPowersDecStep = 8;
7733 
7734  static constexpr cached_power kCachedPowers[] =
7735  {
7736  { 0xAB70FE17C79AC6CA, -1060, -300 },

7817  // This computation gives exactly the same results for k as
7818  // k = ceil((kAlpha - e - 1) * 0.30102999566398114)
7819  // for |e| <= 1500, but doesn't require floating-point operations.
7820  // NB: log_10(2) ~= 78913 / 2^18
7821  assert(e >= -1500);
7822  assert(e <= 1500);
7823  const int f = kAlpha - e - 1;
7824  const int k = (f * 78913) / (1 << 18) + (f > 0);
7825 
7826  const int index = (-kCachedPowersMinDecExp + k + (kCachedPowersDecStep - 1)) / kCachedPowersDecStep;
7827  assert(index >= 0);
7828  assert(index < kCachedPowersSize);
7829  static_cast<void>(kCachedPowersSize); // Fix warning.
7830 
7831  const cached_power cached = kCachedPowers[index];
7832  assert(kAlpha <= cached.e + e + 64);
7833  assert(kGamma >= cached.e + e + 64);
7834 
7835  return cached;
7836 }
7837 
7842 inline int find_largest_pow10(const uint32_t n, uint32_t& pow10)
7843 {
7844  // LCOV_EXCL_START
7845  if (n >= 1000000000)
7846  {
7847  pow10 = 1000000000;
7848  return 10;
7849  }
7850  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
7851  else if (n >= 100000000)
7852  {
7853  pow10 = 100000000;
7854  return 9;
7855  }
7856  else if (n >= 10000000)
7857  {
7858  pow10 = 10000000;
7859  return 8;
7860  }
7861  else if (n >= 1000000)
7862  {
7863  pow10 = 1000000;
7864  return 7;
7865  }
7866  else if (n >= 100000)
7867  {
7868  pow10 = 100000;
7869  return 6;
7870  }
7871  else if (n >= 10000)
7872  {
7873  pow10 = 10000;
7874  return 5;
7875  }
7876  else if (n >= 1000)
7877  {
7878  pow10 = 1000;
7879  return 4;
7880  }
7881  else if (n >= 100)
7882  {
7883  pow10 = 100;
7884  return 3;
7885  }
7886  else if (n >= 10)
7887  {
7888  pow10 = 10;
7889  return 2;
7890  }
7891  else
7892  {
7893  pow10 = 1;
7894  return 1;
7895  }
7896 }
7897 
7898 inline void grisu2_round(char* buf, int len, uint64_t dist, uint64_t delta,
7899  uint64_t rest, uint64_t ten_k)
7900 {
7901  assert(len >= 1);
7902  assert(dist <= delta);
7903  assert(rest <= delta);
7904  assert(ten_k > 0);
7905 
7906  // <--------------------------- delta ---->
7907  // <---- dist --------->
7908  // --------------[------------------+-------------------]--------------
7909  // M- w M+
7910  //
7911  // ten_k
7912  // <------>
7913  // <---- rest ---->
7914  // --------------[------------------+----+--------------]--------------
7915  // w V
7916  // = buf * 10^k
7917  //
7918  // ten_k represents a unit-in-the-last-place in the decimal representation
7919  // stored in buf.
7920  // Decrement buf by ten_k while this takes buf closer to w.
7921 
7922  // The tests are written in this order to avoid overflow in unsigned
7923  // integer arithmetic.
7924 
7925  while (rest < dist
7926  and delta - rest >= ten_k
7927  and (rest + ten_k < dist or dist - rest > rest + ten_k - dist))
7928  {
7929  assert(buf[len - 1] != '0');
7930  buf[len - 1]--;
7931  rest += ten_k;
7932  }
7933 }
7934 
7939 inline void grisu2_digit_gen(char* buffer, int& length, int& decimal_exponent,
7940  diyfp M_minus, diyfp w, diyfp M_plus)
7941 {
7942  static_assert(kAlpha >= -60, "internal error");
7943  static_assert(kGamma <= -32, "internal error");
7944 
7945  // Generates the digits (and the exponent) of a decimal floating-point
7946  // number V = buffer * 10^decimal_exponent in the range [M-, M+]. The diyfp's
7947  // w, M- and M+ share the same exponent e, which satisfies alpha <= e <= gamma.
7948  //
7949  // <--------------------------- delta ---->
7950  // <---- dist --------->
7951  // --------------[------------------+-------------------]--------------
7952  // M- w M+
7953  //
7954  // Grisu2 generates the digits of M+ from left to right and stops as soon as
7955  // V is in [M-,M+].
7956 
7957  assert(M_plus.e >= kAlpha);
7958  assert(M_plus.e <= kGamma);
7959 
7960  uint64_t delta = diyfp::sub(M_plus, M_minus).f; // (significand of (M+ - M-), implicit exponent is e)
7961  uint64_t dist = diyfp::sub(M_plus, w ).f; // (significand of (M+ - w ), implicit exponent is e)
7962 
7963  // Split M+ = f * 2^e into two parts p1 and p2 (note: e < 0):
7964  //
7965  // M+ = f * 2^e
7966  // = ((f div 2^-e) * 2^-e + (f mod 2^-e)) * 2^e
7967  // = ((p1 ) * 2^-e + (p2 )) * 2^e
7968  // = p1 + p2 * 2^e
7969 
7970  const diyfp one(uint64_t{1} << -M_plus.e, M_plus.e);
7971 
7972  uint32_t p1 = static_cast<uint32_t>(M_plus.f >> -one.e); // p1 = f div 2^-e (Since -e >= 32, p1 fits into a 32-bit int.)
7973  uint64_t p2 = M_plus.f & (one.f - 1); // p2 = f mod 2^-e
7974 
7975  // 1)
7976  //
7977  // Generate the digits of the integral part p1 = d[n-1]...d[1]d[0]
7978 
7979  assert(p1 > 0);
7980 
7981  uint32_t pow10;
7982  const int k = find_largest_pow10(p1, pow10);
7983 
7984  // 10^(k-1) <= p1 < 10^k, pow10 = 10^(k-1)
7985  //
7986  // p1 = (p1 div 10^(k-1)) * 10^(k-1) + (p1 mod 10^(k-1))
7987  // = (d[k-1] ) * 10^(k-1) + (p1 mod 10^(k-1))
7988  //
7989  // M+ = p1 + p2 * 2^e
7990  // = d[k-1] * 10^(k-1) + (p1 mod 10^(k-1)) + p2 * 2^e
7991  // = d[k-1] * 10^(k-1) + ((p1 mod 10^(k-1)) * 2^-e + p2) * 2^e
7992  // = d[k-1] * 10^(k-1) + ( rest) * 2^e
7993  //
7994  // Now generate the digits d[n] of p1 from left to right (n = k-1,...,0)
7995  //
7996  // p1 = d[k-1]...d[n] * 10^n + d[n-1]...d[0]
7997  //
7998  // but stop as soon as
7999  //
8000  // rest * 2^e = (d[n-1]...d[0] * 2^-e + p2) * 2^e <= delta * 2^e
8001 
8002  int n = k;
8003  while (n > 0)
8004  {
8005  // Invariants:
8006  // M+ = buffer * 10^n + (p1 + p2 * 2^e) (buffer = 0 for n = k)
8007  // pow10 = 10^(n-1) <= p1 < 10^n
8008  //
8009  const uint32_t d = p1 / pow10; // d = p1 div 10^(n-1)
8010  const uint32_t r = p1 % pow10; // r = p1 mod 10^(n-1)
8011  //
8012  // M+ = buffer * 10^n + (d * 10^(n-1) + r) + p2 * 2^e
8013  // = (buffer * 10 + d) * 10^(n-1) + (r + p2 * 2^e)
8014  //
8015  assert(d <= 9);
8016  buffer[length++] = static_cast<char>('0' + d); // buffer := buffer * 10 + d
8017  //
8018  // M+ = buffer * 10^(n-1) + (r + p2 * 2^e)
8019  //
8020  p1 = r;
8021  n--;
8022  //
8023  // M+ = buffer * 10^n + (p1 + p2 * 2^e)
8024  // pow10 = 10^n
8025  //
8026 
8027  // Now check if enough digits have been generated.
8028  // Compute
8029  //
8030  // p1 + p2 * 2^e = (p1 * 2^-e + p2) * 2^e = rest * 2^e
8031  //
8032  // Note:
8033  // Since rest and delta share the same exponent e, it suffices to
8034  // compare the significands.
8035  const uint64_t rest = (uint64_t{p1} << -one.e) + p2;
8036  if (rest <= delta)
8037  {
8038  // V = buffer * 10^n, with M- <= V <= M+.
8039 
8040  decimal_exponent += n;
8041 
8042  // We may now just stop. But instead look if the buffer could be
8043  // decremented to bring V closer to w.
8044  //
8045  // pow10 = 10^n is now 1 ulp in the decimal representation V.
8046  // The rounding procedure works with diyfp's with an implicit
8047  // exponent of e.
8048  //
8049  // 10^n = (10^n * 2^-e) * 2^e = ulp * 2^e
8050  //
8051  const uint64_t ten_n = uint64_t{pow10} << -one.e;
8052  grisu2_round(buffer, length, dist, delta, rest, ten_n);
8053 
8054  return;
8055  }
8056 
8057  pow10 /= 10;
8058  //
8059  // pow10 = 10^(n-1) <= p1 < 10^n
8060  // Invariants restored.
8061  }
8062 
8063  // 2)
8064  //
8065  // The digits of the integral part have been generated:
8066  //
8067  // M+ = d[k-1]...d[1]d[0] + p2 * 2^e
8068  // = buffer + p2 * 2^e
8069  //
8070  // Now generate the digits of the fractional part p2 * 2^e.
8071  //
8072  // Note:
8073  // No decimal point is generated: the exponent is adjusted instead.
8074  //
8075  // p2 actually represents the fraction
8076  //
8077  // p2 * 2^e
8078  // = p2 / 2^-e
8079  // = d[-1] / 10^1 + d[-2] / 10^2 + ...
8080  //
8081  // Now generate the digits d[-m] of p1 from left to right (m = 1,2,...)
8082  //
8083  // p2 * 2^e = d[-1]d[-2]...d[-m] * 10^-m
8084  // + 10^-m * (d[-m-1] / 10^1 + d[-m-2] / 10^2 + ...)
8085  //
8086  // using
8087  //
8088  // 10^m * p2 = ((10^m * p2) div 2^-e) * 2^-e + ((10^m * p2) mod 2^-e)
8089  // = ( d) * 2^-e + ( r)
8090  //
8091  // or
8092  // 10^m * p2 * 2^e = d + r * 2^e
8093  //
8094  // i.e.
8095  //
8096  // M+ = buffer + p2 * 2^e
8097  // = buffer + 10^-m * (d + r * 2^e)
8098  // = (buffer * 10^m + d) * 10^-m + 10^-m * r * 2^e
8099  //
8100  // and stop as soon as 10^-m * r * 2^e <= delta * 2^e
8101 
8102  assert(p2 > delta);
8103 
8104  int m = 0;
8105  for (;;)
8106  {
8107  // Invariant:
8108  // M+ = buffer * 10^-m + 10^-m * (d[-m-1] / 10 + d[-m-2] / 10^2 + ...) * 2^e
8109  // = buffer * 10^-m + 10^-m * (p2 ) * 2^e
8110  // = buffer * 10^-m + 10^-m * (1/10 * (10 * p2) ) * 2^e
8111  // = buffer * 10^-m + 10^-m * (1/10 * ((10*p2 div 2^-e) * 2^-e + (10*p2 mod 2^-e)) * 2^e
8112  //
8113  assert(p2 <= UINT64_MAX / 10);
8114  p2 *= 10;
8115  const uint64_t d = p2 >> -one.e; // d = (10 * p2) div 2^-e
8116  const uint64_t r = p2 & (one.f - 1); // r = (10 * p2) mod 2^-e
8117  //
8118  // M+ = buffer * 10^-m + 10^-m * (1/10 * (d * 2^-e + r) * 2^e
8119  // = buffer * 10^-m + 10^-m * (1/10 * (d + r * 2^e))
8120  // = (buffer * 10 + d) * 10^(-m-1) + 10^(-m-1) * r * 2^e
8121  //
8122  assert(d <= 9);
8123  buffer[length++] = static_cast<char>('0' + d); // buffer := buffer * 10 + d
8124  //
8125  // M+ = buffer * 10^(-m-1) + 10^(-m-1) * r * 2^e
8126  //
8127  p2 = r;
8128  m++;
8129  //
8130  // M+ = buffer * 10^-m + 10^-m * p2 * 2^e
8131  // Invariant restored.
8132 
8133  // Check if enough digits have been generated.
8134  //
8135  // 10^-m * p2 * 2^e <= delta * 2^e
8136  // p2 * 2^e <= 10^m * delta * 2^e
8137  // p2 <= 10^m * delta
8138  delta *= 10;
8139  dist *= 10;
8140  if (p2 <= delta)
8141  {
8142  break;
8143  }
8144  }
8145 
8146  // V = buffer * 10^-m, with M- <= V <= M+.
8147 
8148  decimal_exponent -= m;
8149 
8150  // 1 ulp in the decimal representation is now 10^-m.
8151  // Since delta and dist are now scaled by 10^m, we need to do the
8152  // same with ulp in order to keep the units in sync.
8153  //
8154  // 10^m * 10^-m = 1 = 2^-e * 2^e = ten_m * 2^e
8155  //
8156  const uint64_t ten_m = one.f;
8157  grisu2_round(buffer, length, dist, delta, p2, ten_m);
8158 
8159  // By construction this algorithm generates the shortest possible decimal
8160  // number (Loitsch, Theorem 6.2) which rounds back to w.
8161  // For an input number of precision p, at least
8162  //
8163  // N = 1 + ceil(p * log_10(2))
8164  //
8165  // decimal digits are sufficient to identify all binary floating-point
8166  // numbers (Matula, "In-and-Out conversions").
8167  // This implies that the algorithm does not produce more than N decimal
8168  // digits.
8169  //
8170  // N = 17 for p = 53 (IEEE double precision)
8171  // N = 9 for p = 24 (IEEE single precision)
8172 }
8173 
8179 inline void grisu2(char* buf, int& len, int& decimal_exponent,
8180  diyfp m_minus, diyfp v, diyfp m_plus)
8181 {
8182  assert(m_plus.e == m_minus.e);
8183  assert(m_plus.e == v.e);
8184 
8185  // --------(-----------------------+-----------------------)-------- (A)
8186  // m- v m+
8187  //
8188  // --------------------(-----------+-----------------------)-------- (B)
8189  // m- v m+
8190  //
8191  // First scale v (and m- and m+) such that the exponent is in the range
8192  // [alpha, gamma].
8193 
8194  const cached_power cached = get_cached_power_for_binary_exponent(m_plus.e);
8195 
8196  const diyfp c_minus_k(cached.f, cached.e); // = c ~= 10^-k
8197 
8198  // The exponent of the products is = v.e + c_minus_k.e + q and is in the range [alpha,gamma]
8199  const diyfp w = diyfp::mul(v, c_minus_k);
8200  const diyfp w_minus = diyfp::mul(m_minus, c_minus_k);
8201  const diyfp w_plus = diyfp::mul(m_plus, c_minus_k);
8202 
8203  // ----(---+---)---------------(---+---)---------------(---+---)----
8204  // w- w w+
8205  // = c*m- = c*v = c*m+
8206  //
8207  // diyfp::mul rounds its result and c_minus_k is approximated too. w, w- and
8208  // w+ are now off by a small amount.
8209  // In fact:
8210  //
8211  // w - v * 10^k < 1 ulp
8212  //
8213  // To account for this inaccuracy, add resp. subtract 1 ulp.
8214  //
8215  // --------+---[---------------(---+---)---------------]---+--------
8216  // w- M- w M+ w+
8217  //
8218  // Now any number in [M-, M+] (bounds included) will round to w when input,
8219  // regardless of how the input rounding algorithm breaks ties.
8220  //
8221  // And digit_gen generates the shortest possible such number in [M-, M+].
8222  // Note that this does not mean that Grisu2 always generates the shortest
8223  // possible number in the interval (m-, m+).
8224  const diyfp M_minus(w_minus.f + 1, w_minus.e);
8225  const diyfp M_plus (w_plus.f - 1, w_plus.e );
8226 
8227  decimal_exponent = -cached.k; // = -(-k) = k
8228 
8229  grisu2_digit_gen(buf, len, decimal_exponent, M_minus, w, M_plus);
8230 }
8231 
8237 template <typename FloatType>
8238 void grisu2(char* buf, int& len, int& decimal_exponent, FloatType value)
8239 {
8240  static_assert(diyfp::kPrecision >= std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::digits + 3,
8241  "internal error: not enough precision");
8242 
8243  assert(std::isfinite(value));
8244  assert(value > 0);
8245 
8246  // If the neighbors (and boundaries) of 'value' are always computed for double-precision
8247  // numbers, all float's can be recovered using strtod (and strtof). However, the resulting
8248  // decimal representations are not exactly "short".
8249  //
8250  // The documentation for 'std::to_chars' (http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/utility/to_chars)
8251  // says "value is converted to a string as if by std::sprintf in the default ("C") locale"
8252  // and since sprintf promotes float's to double's, I think this is exactly what 'std::to_chars'
8253  // does.
8254  // On the other hand, the documentation for 'std::to_chars' requires that "parsing the
8255  // representation using the corresponding std::from_chars function recovers value exactly". That
8256  // indicates that single precision floating-point numbers should be recovered using
8257  // 'std::strtof'.
8258  //
8259  // NB: If the neighbors are computed for single-precision numbers, there is a single float
8260  // (7.0385307e-26f) which can't be recovered using strtod. The resulting double precision
8261  // value is off by 1 ulp.
8262 #if 0
8263  const boundaries w = compute_boundaries(static_cast<double>(value));
8264 #else
8265  const boundaries w = compute_boundaries(value);
8266 #endif
8267 
8268  grisu2(buf, len, decimal_exponent, w.minus, w.w, w.plus);
8269 }
8270 
8276 inline char* append_exponent(char* buf, int e)
8277 {
8278  assert(e > -1000);
8279  assert(e < 1000);
8280 
8281  if (e < 0)
8282  {
8283  e = -e;
8284  *buf++ = '-';
8285  }
8286  else
8287  {
8288  *buf++ = '+';
8289  }
8290 
8291  uint32_t k = static_cast<uint32_t>(e);
8292  if (k < 10)
8293  {
8294  // Always print at least two digits in the exponent.
8295  // This is for compatibility with printf("%g").
8296  *buf++ = '0';
8297  *buf++ = static_cast<char>('0' + k);
8298  }
8299  else if (k < 100)
8300  {
8301  *buf++ = static_cast<char>('0' + k / 10);
8302  k %= 10;
8303  *buf++ = static_cast<char>('0' + k);
8304  }
8305  else
8306  {
8307  *buf++ = static_cast<char>('0' + k / 100);
8308  k %= 100;
8309  *buf++ = static_cast<char>('0' + k / 10);
8310  k %= 10;
8311  *buf++ = static_cast<char>('0' + k);
8312  }
8313 
8314  return buf;
8315 }
8316 
8326 inline char* format_buffer(char* buf, int len, int decimal_exponent,
8327  int min_exp, int max_exp)
8328 {
8329  assert(min_exp < 0);
8330  assert(max_exp > 0);
8331 
8332  const int k = len;
8333  const int n = len + decimal_exponent;
8334 
8335  // v = buf * 10^(n-k)
8336  // k is the length of the buffer (number of decimal digits)
8337  // n is the position of the decimal point relative to the start of the buffer.
8338 
8339  if (k <= n and n <= max_exp)
8340  {
8341  // digits[000]
8342  // len <= max_exp + 2
8343 
8344  std::memset(buf + k, '0', static_cast<size_t>(n - k));
8345  // Make it look like a floating-point number (#362, #378)
8346  buf[n + 0] = '.';
8347  buf[n + 1] = '0';
8348  return buf + (n + 2);
8349  }
8350 
8351  if (0 < n and n <= max_exp)
8352  {
8353  // dig.its
8354  // len <= max_digits10 + 1
8355 
8356  assert(k > n);
8357 
8358  std::memmove(buf + (n + 1), buf + n, static_cast<size_t>(k - n));
8359  buf[n] = '.';
8360  return buf + (k + 1);
8361  }
8362 
8363  if (min_exp < n and n <= 0)
8364  {
8365  // 0.[000]digits
8366  // len <= 2 + (-min_exp - 1) + max_digits10
8367 
8368  std::memmove(buf + (2 + -n), buf, static_cast<size_t>(k));
8369  buf[0] = '0';
8370  buf[1] = '.';
8371  std::memset(buf + 2, '0', static_cast<size_t>(-n));
8372  return buf + (2 + (-n) + k);
8373  }
8374 
8375  if (k == 1)
8376  {
8377  // dE+123
8378  // len <= 1 + 5
8379 
8380  buf += 1;
8381  }
8382  else
8383  {
8384  // d.igitsE+123
8385  // len <= max_digits10 + 1 + 5
8386 
8387  std::memmove(buf + 2, buf + 1, static_cast<size_t>(k - 1));
8388  buf[1] = '.';
8389  buf += 1 + k;
8390  }
8391 
8392  *buf++ = 'e';
8393  return append_exponent(buf, n - 1);
8394 }
8395 
8396 } // namespace dtoa_impl
8397 
8408 template <typename FloatType>
8409 char* to_chars(char* first, char* last, FloatType value)
8410 {
8411  static_cast<void>(last); // maybe unused - fix warning
8412  assert(std::isfinite(value));
8413 
8414  // Use signbit(value) instead of (value < 0) since signbit works for -0.
8415  if (std::signbit(value))
8416  {
8417  value = -value;
8418  *first++ = '-';
8419  }
8420 
8421  if (value == 0) // +-0
8422  {
8423  *first++ = '0';
8424  // Make it look like a floating-point number (#362, #378)
8425  *first++ = '.';
8426  *first++ = '0';
8427  return first;
8428  }
8429 
8430  assert(last - first >= std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::max_digits10);
8431 
8432  // Compute v = buffer * 10^decimal_exponent.
8433  // The decimal digits are stored in the buffer, which needs to be interpreted
8434  // as an unsigned decimal integer.
8435  // len is the length of the buffer, i.e. the number of decimal digits.
8436  int len = 0;
8437  int decimal_exponent = 0;
8438  dtoa_impl::grisu2(first, len, decimal_exponent, value);
8439 
8440  assert(len <= std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::max_digits10);
8441 
8442  // Format the buffer like printf("%.*g", prec, value)
8443  constexpr int kMinExp = -4;
8444  // Use digits10 here to increase compatibility with version 2.
8445  constexpr int kMaxExp = std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::digits10;
8446 
8447  assert(last - first >= kMaxExp + 2);
8448  assert(last - first >= 2 + (-kMinExp - 1) + std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::max_digits10);
8449  assert(last - first >= std::numeric_limits<FloatType>::max_digits10 + 6);
8450 
8451  return dtoa_impl::format_buffer(first, len, decimal_exponent, kMinExp, kMaxExp);
8452 }

8471 // serialization //
